2391 // Reset parameters to their defaults
2392 void US_Edit::reset( void )

2397  floatingData = false;

2399  step = MENISCUS;
2400  meniscus = 0.0;

2407  bl_corr_right_x = 9.0;

2653 // Do a Gap check against threshold value
2654 void US_Edit::gap_check( void )
2655 {
2656  int threshold = (int)ct_gaps->value();
2657  gap_thresh = ct_gaps->value();
2658 
2659  US_DataIO::Scan s;
2660  QString gaps;
2661 
2662  int scanNumber = 0;
2663  int rawScanNumber = -1;
2664  bool deleteAll = false;
2665 
2666  foreach ( s, data.scanData )
2667  {
2668  rawScanNumber++;
2669  // If scan has been deleted, skip to next
2670  if ( ! includes.contains( scanNumber ) ) continue;
2671 
2672  int maxGap = 0;
2673  int gapLength = 0;
2674  int location = 0;
2675 
2676  int leftPoint = data.xindex( range_left );
2677  int rightPoint = data.xindex( range_right );
2678 
2679  for ( int i = leftPoint; i <= rightPoint; i++ )
2680  {
2681  int byte = i / 8;
2682  int bit = i % 8;
2683 
2684  if ( s.interpolated[ byte ] & 1 << ( 7 - bit ) )
2685  gapLength++;
2686  else
2687  gapLength = 0;
2688 
2689  if ( gapLength > maxGap )
2690  {
2691  maxGap = gapLength;
2692  location = i;
2693  }
2694  }
2695 
2696  if ( maxGap >= threshold )
2697  {
2698  QwtPlotCurve* curve = NULL;
2699  bool deleteCurrent = false;
2700 
2701  // Hightlight scan
2702  ct_to->setValue( 0.0 ); // Unfocus everything
2703 
2704  QString seconds = QString::number( s.seconds );
2705  QwtPlotItemList items = data_plot->itemList();
2706 
2707  for ( int i = 0; i < items.size(); i++ )
2708  {
2709  if ( items[ i ]->rtti() == QwtPlotItem::Rtti_PlotCurve )
2710  {
2711  if ( items[ i ]->title().text().contains( seconds ) )
2712  {
2713  curve = dynamic_cast< QwtPlotCurve* >( items[ i ] );
2714  break;
2715  }
2716  }
2717  }
2718 
2719  if ( curve == NULL )
2720  {
2721  qDebug() << "Cannot find curve during gap check";
2722  return;
2723  }
2724 
2725  // Popup unless delete all is set
2726  if ( ! deleteAll )
2727  {
2728  // Color the selected point
2729  QPen p = curve->pen();
2730  QBrush b = curve->brush();
2731 
2732  p.setColor( Qt::red );
2733  b.setColor( Qt::red );
2734 
2735  curve->setPen ( p );
2736  curve->setBrush( b );
2737  data_plot->replot();
2738 
2739  // Ask the user what to do
2740  QMessageBox box;
2741 
2742  box.setWindowTitle( tr( "Excessive Scan Gaps Detected" ) );
2743 
2744  double radius = data.xvalues[ 0 ] + location * s.delta_r;
2745 
2746  gaps = tr( "Scan " )
2747  + QString::number( rawScanNumber )
2748  + tr( " has a maximum reading gap of " )
2749  + QString::number( maxGap )
2750  + tr( " starting at radius " )
2751  + QString::number( radius, 'f', 3 );
2752 
2753  box.setText( gaps );
2754  box.setInformativeText( tr( "Delete?" ) );
2755 
2756  QPushButton* pb_delete = box.addButton( tr( "Delete" ),
2757  QMessageBox::YesRole );
2758 
2759  QPushButton* pb_deleteAll = box.addButton( tr( "Delete All" ),
2760  QMessageBox::AcceptRole );
2761 
2762  QPushButton* pb_skip = box.addButton( tr( "Skip" ),
2763  QMessageBox::NoRole );
2764 
2765  QPushButton* pb_cancel = box.addButton( tr( "Cancel" ),
2766  QMessageBox::RejectRole );
2767 
2768  box.setEscapeButton ( pb_cancel );
2769  box.setDefaultButton( pb_delete );
2770 
2771  box.exec();
2772 
2773  if ( box.clickedButton() == pb_delete )
2774  deleteCurrent = true;
2775 
2776  else if ( box.clickedButton() == pb_deleteAll )
2777  {
2778  deleteAll = true;
2779  deleteCurrent = true;
2780  }
2781 
2782  else
2783  {
2784  // Uncolor scan
2785  p.setColor( Qt::yellow );
2786  b.setColor( Qt::yellow );
2787 
2788  curve->setPen ( p );
2789  curve->setBrush( b );
2790  data_plot->replot();
2791  }
2792 
2793  if ( box.clickedButton() == pb_skip )
2794  continue;
2795 
2796  if ( box.clickedButton() == pb_cancel )
2797  return;
2798  }
2799 
2800  // Delete the scan
2801  if ( deleteAll || deleteCurrent )
2802  {
2803  includes.removeOne( scanNumber );
2804  replot();
2805 
2806  ct_to ->setMaximum( includes.size() );
2807  ct_from->setMaximum( includes.size() );
2808  }
2809  }
2810 
2811  scanNumber++;
2812  }
2813 }

2920 //Slot to process optics type...
2921 void US_Edit::process_optics_auto( )
2922 {
2923  all_loaded = false;
2924  editProfile.clear();
2925  editProfile_includes. clear();
2926  editProfile_blc. clear();
2927  editProfile_scans_excl.clear();
2928  automatic_meniscus.clear();
2929  manual_edit_comments. clear();
2930  centerpieceParameters.clear();
2931  aprofileParameters.clear();
2932  iwavl_edit_ref.clear();
2933  iwavl_edit_ref_index.clear();
2934  triple_plot_first_time.clear();
2935 
2936  //abde
2937  edited_triples_abde. clear();
2938 
2939  //Read centerpiece names from protocol:
2940  centerpiece_names.clear();
2941 
2942  QList< DataDesc_auto > sdescs_auto;
2943  datamap.clear();
2944 
2945  scan_db_auto();
2946  sdescs_auto = datamap.values();
2947  load_db_auto( sdescs_auto );
2948 
2949  runID = workingDir.section( "/", -1, -1 );
2950 DbgLv(1) << "Ld: runID" << runID << "wdir" << workingDir;
2951  sData .clear();
2952  sd_offs .clear();
2953  sd_knts .clear();
2954  cb_triple->clear();
2955  files .clear();
2956 
2957  if ( triples.size() == 0 )
2958  {
2959  QMessageBox::warning( this,
2960  tr( "No Files Found" ),
2961  tr( "There were no files of the form *.auc\n"
2962  "found in the specified directory." ) );
2963  return;
2964  }
2965 
2966  qDebug() << "IN PROCESS OPTICS: triples_size() " << triples.size();
2967 
2968  cb_triple->addItems( triples );
2969 
2970  // Debug
2971  for (int index = 0; index < cb_triple->count(); index++)
2972  qDebug() << cb_triple->itemText(index);
2973 
2974  connect( cb_triple, SIGNAL( currentIndexChanged( int ) ),
2975  SLOT ( new_triple_auto ( int ) ) );
2976  triple_index = 0;
2977  data_index = 0;
2978 
2979  le_info->setText( runID );
2980 
2981  data = allData[ 0 ];
2982  dataType = QString( QChar( data.type[ 0 ] ) )
2983  + QString( QChar( data.type[ 1 ] ) );
2984 
2985  if ( dataType == "IP" )
2986  {
2987  lb_gaps->setText( tr( "Fringe Tolerance" ) );
2988 
2989  ct_gaps->setRange ( 0.0, 20.0 );
2990  ct_gaps->setSingleStep( 0.001 );
2991  ct_gaps->setValue ( 0.4 );
2992  ct_gaps->setNumButtons( 3 );
2993 
2994  connect( ct_gaps, SIGNAL( valueChanged ( double ) ),
2995  SLOT ( set_fringe_tolerance( double ) ) );
2996  }
2997  else
2998  {
2999  lb_gaps->setText( tr( "Threshold for Scan Gaps" ) );
3000 
3001  ct_gaps->disconnect ();
3002  ct_gaps->setRange ( 10.0, 100.0 );
3003  ct_gaps->setSingleStep( 10.0 );
3004  ct_gaps->setValue ( 50.0 );
3005  ct_gaps->setNumButtons( 1 );
3006  }
3007 
3008  QString runtype = runID + "." + dataType;
3009 DbgLv(1) << "Ld: runtype" << runtype;
3010  nwaveln = 0;
3011  ncelchn = 0;
3012  outData.clear();
3013 
3014  qDebug() << "EDIT: triples -- " << triples;
3015 
3016  for ( int trx = 0; trx < triples.size(); trx++ )
3017  { // Generate file names
3018  QString triple = QString( triples.at( trx ) ).replace( " / ", "." );
3019  QString file = runtype + "." + triple + ".auc";
3020  files << file;
3021 
3022  qDebug() << "EDIT: file -- " << file;
3023 
3024  // Save pointers as initial output data vector
3025  outData << &allData[ trx ];
3026 
3027  QString scell = triple.section( ".", 0, 0 ).simplified();
3028  QString schan = triple.section( ".", 1, 1 ).simplified();
3029  QString swavl = triple.section( ".", 2, 2 ).simplified();
3030 
3031  if ( ! rawc_wvlns.contains( swavl ) )
3032  { // Accumulate wavelengths in case this is MWL
3033  nwaveln++;
3034  rawc_wvlns << swavl;
3035  }
3036 
3037  nwavelo = nwaveln;
3038  QString celchn = scell + " / " + schan;
3039 
3040  if ( ! celchns.contains( celchn ) )
3041  { // Accumulate cell/channel values in case this is MWL
3042  ncelchn++;
3043  celchns << celchn;
3044  }
3045  }
3046 DbgLv(1) << "rawc_wvlns size" << rawc_wvlns.size() << nwaveln;
3047 DbgLv(1) << " celchns size" << celchns.size() << ncelchn;
3048  QMap<int, QString> m;
3049  for (const auto& s : rawc_wvlns) m[s.toInt()] = s;
3050  rawc_wvlns = QStringList(m.values());
3051  rawi_wvlns.clear();
3052  toti_wvlns.clear();
3053 
3054  for ( int wvx = 0; wvx < nwaveln; wvx++ )
3055  {
3056  int iwavl = rawc_wvlns[ wvx ].toInt();
3057  rawi_wvlns << iwavl;
3058  toti_wvlns << iwavl;
3059  }
3060 
3061  workingDir = workingDir + "/";
3062  QString file = workingDir + runtype + ".xml";
3063  expType = "";
3064  QFile xf( file );
3065 
3066  if ( xf.open( QIODevice::ReadOnly | QIODevice::Text ) )
3067  {
3068  QXmlStreamReader xml( &xf );
3069 
3070  while( ! xml.atEnd() )
3071  {
3072  xml.readNext();
3073 
3074  if ( xml.isStartElement() && xml.name() == "experiment" )
3075  {
3076  QXmlStreamAttributes xa = xml.attributes();
3077  expType = xa.value( "type" ).toString();
3078  break;
3079  }
3080  }
3081 
3082  xf.close();
3083  }
3084 
3085  if ( expType.isEmpty() && disk_controls->db() )
3086  { // no experiment type yet and data read from DB: try for DB exp type
3087  if ( dbP == NULL )

4061 bool US_Edit::readProtocolCells_auto( QXmlStreamReader& xmli )
4062 {
4063  while( ! xmli.atEnd() )
4064  {
4065  QString ename = xmli.name().toString();
4066 
4067  if ( xmli.isStartElement() )
4068  {
4069  if ( ename == "cell" )
4070  {
4071  QXmlStreamAttributes attr = xmli.attributes();
4072  QString centerpiece = attr.value( "centerpiece" ).toString();
4073  QString cell_id = attr.value( "id" ).toString();
4074 
4075  cell_to_centerpiece [ cell_id ] = centerpiece;
4076  }
4077  }
4078 
4079  bool was_end = xmli.isEndElement(); // Just read was End of element?
4080  xmli.readNext(); // Read the next element
4081 
4082  if ( was_end && ename == "cells" ) // Break after "</cells>"
4083  break;
4084  }
4085 
4086  return ( ! xmli.hasError() );
4087 }

4255 // Return a flag if an XML attribute string represents true or false.

4321 
4322 QVector<double> US_Edit::find_airGap_interference_auto()
4323 {
4324  QVector<double> airGap_vals;
4325  QVector< double > x_airGap_lefts;
4326  QVector< double > x_airGap_rights;
4327  double airGap_left_av = 0;
4328  double airGap_right_av = 0;
4329 
4330  // starting from meniscus position, go backwards and fit several points into staight line..
4331  // then, look at max deviation from it and find the onset of the airGap (in reverse order)
4332  // basically, repeat finding meniscus algorithm...
4333 
4334  // For each scan in the last ~20% of scans:
4335  int start_scan = int(0.8*data.scanData.size());
4336  int end_scan = data.scanData.size();
4337 
4338  for ( int i = start_scan; i < end_scan; i++ )
4339  {
4340  US_DataIO::Scan* s = &data.scanData[ i ];
4341 
4342  double y_max_deviation = -1.0e99;
4343  double x_airGap_left;
4344  double x_airGap_right;
4345 
4346  double right_fit = meniscus - 0.02;
4347  int indexRight_fit = data.xindex( right_fit );
4348  double left_fit = right_fit - 0.02;
4349  int indexLeft_fit = data.xindex( left_fit );
4350 
4351  //qDebug() << "INTERFERENCE: left_fit, right_fit: " << left_fit << ", " << right_fit;
4352 
4353  /**********************
4354  //Find a fit to straight line
4355  double sumX = 0;
4356  double sumY = 0;
4357  double sumXY = 0;
4358  double sumX2 = 0;
4359  int countPoints = 0;
4360 
4361  for ( int j = indexLeft_fit; j <= indexRight_fit; j++ )
4362  {
4363  double y_curr = s->rvalues[ j ] * invert;
4364  double x_curr = data.xvalues[ j ];
4365 
4366  sumX += x_curr;
4367  sumY += y_curr;
4368  sumXY += x_curr*y_curr;
4369  sumX2 += x_curr*x_curr;
4370 
4371  ++countPoints;
4372  }
4373 
4374  //Slope && mean: y(x) = Slope * X + YInt;
4375  double xMean = sumX / countPoints;
4376  double yMean = sumY / countPoints;
4377  double Slope = (sumXY - sumX * yMean) / (sumX2 - sumX * xMean);
4378  double YInt = yMean - Slope * xMean;
4379 
4380  ***************/
4381 
4382  /********** TESTITNG *******************************************************/
4383  //Alternative: derive a curve passing through Left/Right indecies
4384  double Slope = (s->rvalues[ indexRight_fit ] * invert - s->rvalues[ indexLeft_fit ] * invert ) / ( data.xvalues[ indexRight_fit ] - data.xvalues[ indexLeft_fit ] );
4385  double YInt = s->rvalues[ indexRight_fit ] * invert - Slope * data.xvalues[ indexRight_fit ];
4386  /****************************************************************************/
4387 
4388  //qDebug() << "y(x) = Slope * X + YInt: " << Slope << "*X + " << YInt;
4389 
4390  //Find the biggest y-deviation from a line fit
4391  for ( int j = indexLeft_fit; j <= indexRight_fit; j++ )
4392  {
4393  double y_curr = s->rvalues[ j ] * invert;
4394  double x_curr = data.xvalues[ j ];
4395 
4396  double y_fit = Slope * x_curr + YInt;
4397  double y_diff_abs = fabs( y_curr - y_fit );
4398 
4399  //qDebug() << "y_curr, x_curr, (Slope * x_curr + YInt), y_diff_abs: " << y_curr << ", " << x_curr << ", " << y_fit << ", " << y_diff_abs;
4400 
4401  if( y_diff_abs > y_max_deviation )
4402  y_max_deviation = y_diff_abs;
4403  }
4404 
4405  //qDebug() << " y_max_deviation: " << y_max_deviation;
4406 
4407  //reverse order: search for a y-deviation (much) bigger than from a straight line fit based on selected points
4408  int indexLeft = data.xindex( 5.85 ); //Begiinning of the cell?
4409  //right_fit -= 0.02;
4410  //indexRight_fit = data.xindex( right_fit );
4411  for ( int j = indexRight_fit; j >= indexLeft; --j )
4412  {
4413  double y_curr = s->rvalues[ j ] * invert;
4414  double x_curr = data.xvalues[ j ];
4415 
4416  double y_diff_abs = fabs( y_curr - (Slope * x_curr + YInt) );
4417 
4418  if( y_diff_abs > y_max_deviation * 1.5 )
4419  {
4420  x_airGap_right = x_curr - 0.02;
4421  x_airGap_left = x_airGap_right - 0.02;
4422  break;
4423  }
4424  }
4425  x_airGap_lefts.push_back( x_airGap_left );
4426  x_airGap_rights.push_back( x_airGap_right );
4427 
4428  //qDebug() << "x_airGap_left, x_airGap_right: " << x_airGap_left << ", " << x_airGap_right;
4429  }
4430 
4431  //Find simple average position of the left/right airGap values
4432  for ( int i=0; i < x_airGap_lefts.size(); i++ )
4433  {
4434  airGap_left_av += x_airGap_lefts[ i ];
4435  airGap_right_av += x_airGap_rights[ i ];
4436  }
4437 
4438  airGap_left_av /= x_airGap_lefts.size();
4439  airGap_right_av /= x_airGap_rights.size();
4440 
4441  // airGap_vals.push_back(airGap_left_av);
4442  // airGap_vals.push_back(airGap_right_av);
4443 
4444  //TEMP
4445  airGap_vals.push_back(5.85);
4446  airGap_vals.push_back(5.90);
4447 
4448 
4449  qDebug() << "INTERFERENCE: airGaps: " << airGap_vals;
4450 
4451  return airGap_vals;
4452 }

4454 double US_Edit::find_meniscus_interference_auto()

4458  double angle_db = centerpiece_info[ "angle" ].toDouble();
4459 
4460  //double aprofile_volume = 460; // Just an example - to be read from AProfile, will be global

4494  double sumY = 0;

4500  {
4501  double y_curr = s->rvalues[ j ] * invert;
4502  double x_curr = data.xvalues[ j ];
4503 
4504  sumX += x_curr;
4505  sumY += y_curr;
4506  sumXY += x_curr*y_curr;
4507  sumX2 += x_curr*x_curr;
4508 
4509  ++countPoints;
4510  }
4511 
4512  //Slope && mean: y(x) = Slope * X + YInt;
4513  double xMean = sumX / countPoints;
4514  double yMean = sumY / countPoints;
4515  double Slope = (sumXY - sumX * yMean) / (sumX2 - sumX * xMean);
4516  double YInt = yMean - Slope * xMean;
4517  **********************************************/
4518 
4519  /********** TESTITNG *******************************************************/
4520  //Alternative: derive a curve passing through Left/Right indecies
4521  double Slope = (s->rvalues[ indexRight ] * invert - s->rvalues[ indexLeft_fit ] * invert ) / ( data.xvalues[ indexRight ] - data.xvalues[ indexLeft_fit ] );
4522  double YInt = s->rvalues[ indexRight ] * invert - Slope * data.xvalues[ indexRight ];
4523  /****************************************************************************/
4524 
4525  //qDebug() << "y(x) = Slope * X + YInt: " << Slope << "*X + " << YInt;
4526

4528  for ( int j = indexLeft_fit; j <= indexRight; j++ )
4529  {
4530  double y_curr = s->rvalues[ j ] * invert;
4531  double x_curr = data.xvalues[ j ];
4532

4534  double y_diff_abs = fabs( y_curr - y_fit );
4535 
4536  //qDebug() << "y_curr, x_curr, (Slope * x_curr + YInt), y_diff_abs: " << y_curr << ", " << x_curr << ", " << y_fit << ", " << y_diff_abs;
4537 
4538  if( y_diff_abs > y_max_deviation )
4539  y_max_deviation = y_diff_abs;
4540  }
4541 
4542  //qDebug() << " y_max_deviation: " << y_max_deviation;
4543 
4544  //reverse order: search for a y-deviation (much) bigger than from a straight line fit based on selected points
4545  int indexLeft = data.xindex( meniscus_init );
4546  for ( int j = indexRight; j >= indexLeft; --j )
4547  {
4548  double y_curr = s->rvalues[ j ] * invert;
4549  double x_curr = data.xvalues[ j ];
4550 
4551  double y_diff_abs = fabs( y_curr - (Slope * x_curr + YInt) );
4552

4554  {
4555  x_meniscus = x_curr;
4556  break;
4557  }
4558  }
4559  x_meniscuses.push_back( x_meniscus );
4560 
4561  }
4562

4565  {

4567  //qDebug() << "x_max: " << x_maxs[ i ] ;
4568  }

4735 // Create the data descriptions map with indecies and counts
4736 void US_Edit::create_descs_auto( QStringList& runIDs, QStringList& infoDs, int naucf )
4737 {
4738  datamap.clear(); // Clear label-descrip map
4739  infoDs .sort(); // Sort concat strings by label
4740 
4741  QString prunid = "";
4742  int tripndx = 1;
4743 
4744  for ( int ii = 0; ii < naucf; ii++ )
4745  {
4746  // Parse values in concatenation
4747  QString idata = infoDs.at( ii );
4748  QString label = idata.section( "^", 0, 0 );
4749  QString runID = idata.section( "^", 1, 1 );
4750  QString tripID = idata.section( "^", 2, 2 );
4751  QString filename = idata.section( "^", 3, 3 );
4752  QString rawGUID = idata.section( "^", 4, 4 );
4753  QString rawDataID = idata.section( "^", 5, 5 );
4754  QString date = idata.section( "^", 6, 6 );
4755  QString dcheck = idata.section( "^", 7, 7 );
4756  QString lkey = runID + "." + tripID;
4757  tripndx = ( runID == prunid ) ? ( tripndx + 1 ) : 1;
4758  prunid = runID;
4759 
4760  // Fill the description object and set count,index
4761  DataDesc_auto ddesc;
4762  ddesc.label = label;
4763  ddesc.runID = runID;
4764  ddesc.tripID = tripID;
4765  ddesc.filename = filename;
4766  ddesc.rawGUID = rawGUID;
4767  ddesc.date = date;
4768  ddesc.dcheck = dcheck;
4769  ddesc.DB_id = rawDataID.toInt();
4770  ddesc.tripknt = runIDs.count( runID );
4771  ddesc.tripndx = tripndx;
4772 
4773 //qDebug() << "CrDe: ii tknt" << ii << ddesc.tripknt << "lkey" << lkey;
4774  if ( datamap.contains( lkey ) )
4775  { // Handle the case where the lkey already exists
4776  qDebug() << "*** DUPLICATE lkey" << lkey << "***";
4777  lkey = lkey + "(2)";
4778 
4779  if ( datamap.contains( lkey ) )
4780  { // Handle two duplicates
4781  lkey = lkey.replace( "(2)", "(3)" );
4782  }
4783  }
4784 
4785  datamap[ lkey ] = ddesc;
4786  }
4787  return;
4788 }

4791 // Load the data from the database
4792 void US_Edit::load_db_auto( QList< DataDesc_auto >& sdescs )
4793 {
4794  int nerr = 0;
4795  QString emsg;
4796  QString rdir = US_Settings::resultDir();
4797  QString runID = sdescs.count() > 0 ? sdescs.at( 0 ).runID : "";
4798  workingDir = rdir + "/" + runID;
4799  allData.clear();
4800  triples.clear();
4801 
4802  QDir work( rdir );
4803  work.mkdir( runID );
4804 
4805  // Connect to DB
4806  US_Passwd pw;
4807  US_DB2 db( pw.getPasswd() );
4808 
4809  if ( db.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
4810  {
4811  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Connection Problem" ),
4812  tr( "Could not connect to database\n " ) + db.lastError() );
4813  return;
4814  }
4815 
4816  for ( int ii = 0; ii < sdescs.count(); ii++ )
4817  { // Loop to load selected data from the database
4818  US_DataIO::RawData rdata;
4819  DataDesc_auto ddesc = sdescs.at( ii );
4820  int idRaw = ddesc.DB_id;
4821  QString filebase = ddesc.filename;
4822  QString filename = workingDir + "/" + filebase;
4823  QString triple = ddesc.tripID.replace( ".", " / " );
4824  QString dcheck = ddesc.dcheck;
4825  bool dload_auc = true;
4826  int stat = 0;
4827 
4828  if ( QFile( filename ).exists() )
4829  { // AUC file exists, do only download if checksum+size mismatch
4830  QString fcheck = US_Util::md5sum_file( filename );
4831 
4832  if ( dcheck.isEmpty() )
4833  {

4840  dcheck = ddesc.dcheck;
4841  }
4842 
4843  dload_auc = ( fcheck != dcheck );
4844  }
4845 
4846  //emit progress( tr( "Loading triple " ) + triple );
4847  qApp->processEvents();
4848 
4849  // Download the DB record to a file (if need be)
4850  if ( dload_auc )
4851  {
4852  db.readBlobFromDB( filename, "download_aucData", idRaw );
4853  int stat = db.lastErrno();
4854

4856  {

4858  emsg += tr( "Error (%1) downloading to file %2\n" )

4865

4867  {

4869  emsg += tr( "Error (%1) reading file %2\n" )
4870  .arg( stat ).arg( filebase );
4871  }
4872 
4873  // Accumulate lists of data and triples
4874  allData << rdata;
4875  triples << triple;
4876  }
4877 }

5468  rpmc += 400.0;

5473  double timec = ds->seconds;
5474  double rpmc = ds->rpm;
5475  w2ti += ( timec - timel ) * sq( rpmc * M_PI / 30.0 );
5476  qDebug() << "scan" << ii+1 << "delta-r rpm seconds" << ds->delta_r
5477  << rpmc << timec << "omega2t w2t-integ" << ds->omega2t << w2ti;

5481  double time1 = timel + deltt;
5482  qDebug() << " scan 1 omega2t-implied time" << time1;
5483  }

5485  }

5997  cb_triple->addItems( celchns );
5998  connect( cb_triple, SIGNAL( currentIndexChanged( int ) ),
5999  SLOT ( new_triple ( int ) ) );
6000  pb_nextChan->setEnabled( celchns.size() > 1 );
6001 
6002  odlimit = 1.8;
6003 
6004  connect_mwl_ctrls( true );
6005 
6006  plot_mwl();
6007  } // END: isMwl=true
6008  else
6009  {
6010  new_triple( 0 );
6011 //*DEBUG* Print times,omega^ts
6012  triple = allData[0];
6013  double timel = triple.scanData[0].rpm / 400.0;
6014  double rpmc = 400.0;
6015  int nstep = (int)timel;
6016  double w2ti = 0.0;
6017  for ( int ii=0; ii<nstep; ii++ )
6018  {
6019  w2ti += sq( rpmc * M_PI / 30.0 );
6020  rpmc += 400.0;
6021  }
6022  for ( int ii=0; ii<triple.scanData.size(); ii++ )
6023  {
6024  US_DataIO::Scan* ds=&triple.scanData[ii];
6025  double timec = ds->seconds;
6026  double rpmc = ds->rpm;
6027  w2ti += ( timec - timel ) * sq( rpmc * M_PI / 30.0 );
6028  qDebug() << "scan" << ii+1 << "delta-r rpm seconds" << ds->delta_r
6029  << rpmc << timec << "omega2t w2t-integ" << ds->omega2t << w2ti;
6030  if(ii==0)
6031  {
6032  double deltt = ds->omega2t / sq(rpmc*M_PI/30.0);
6033  double time1 = timel + deltt;
6034  qDebug() << " scan 1 omega2t-implied time" << time1;
6035  }
6036  timel = timec;
6037  }
6038 //*DEBUG* Print times,omega^ts
6039  }
6040 
6041  // Set up OD limit and any MWL controls
6042  ct_odlim->disconnect();
6043  ct_odlim->setValue( odlimit );
6044  connect( ct_odlim, SIGNAL( valueChanged ( double ) ),
6045  this, SLOT ( od_radius_limit ( double ) ) );
6046 
6047  show_mwl_controls( isMwl );
6048 
6049 
6050  // DEBUG
6051  qDebug() << "meniscus: " << meniscus;
6052  qDebug() << "meniscus_left: " << meniscus_left;
6053  qDebug() << "range_left:" << range_left;
6054  qDebug() << "range_right:" << range_right;
6055  qDebug() << "plateau: " << plateau;
6056  qDebug() << "baseline: " << baseline;
6057 }
6058 
6059 void US_Edit::set_data_over_lamda() {
6060  int trx = 0;
6061  int trx_b = 0;
6062  rdata.clear();
6063  for ( int ccx = 0; ccx < ncelchn; ccx++ )
6064  { // Handle each triple of AUC data
6065  lambdas_by_cell( ccx ); // Lambdas in cell
6066  trx_b = trx;
6067  int min_xval = -100000000;
6068  int max_xval = 100000000;
6069  int dx = 1; // preventing that dx becomes 0 and causing an infinite loop
6070  for ( int jwx = 0; jwx < nwaveln; jwx++ )
6071  {
6072  edata = &allData[ trx ]; // Triple data
6073  min_xval = qMax(min_xval, static_cast<int> (qRound(edata->xvalues.first() * 1000)));
6074  max_xval = qMin(max_xval, static_cast<int> (qRound(edata->xvalues.last() * 1000)));
6075  double d = edata->xvalues.at(1) - edata->xvalues.at(0);
6076  dx = qMax(dx, static_cast<int> (qRound(d * 1000)));
6077  trx++;
6078  }
6079  QVector< double > xvals;
6080  int xx = min_xval;
6081  while (xx <= max_xval)
6082  {
6083  xvals << xx / 1000.0;
6084  xx += dx;
6085  }
6086 
6087  rdata_xvals << xvals;
6088  trx = trx_b;
6089  // order of sorting data:
6090  int nscans = allData[trx].scanCount();
6091  int ndp = xvals.size() * nwaveln * nscans;
6092  QVector< double > yvals(ndp, 0);
6093  QVector< int > xvals_pos(nwaveln, 0);
6094 
6095  for (int ii = 0; ii < xvals.size(); ii++)
6096  {
6097  trx = trx_b;
6098  int txval = static_cast<int>(qRound(xvals.at(ii) * 1000));
6099  for ( int jj = 0; jj < nwaveln; jj++ )
6100  { // Each wavelength in the current cell
6101  edata = &allData[ trx ]; // Triple data
6102  int iwavl = rawi_wvlns[ jj ]; // Wavelength value
6103  int wvx = toti_wvlns.indexOf( iwavl ); // Wavelength index
6104  DbgLv(1) << "IS-MWL: trx ccx wvx" << trx << ccx << wvx;
6105 
6106  int rpidx = -1;
6107  for ( int kk = xvals_pos.at(jj); kk < edata->pointCount(); kk++)
6108  {
6109  int cxval = static_cast<int>(qRound(edata->xvalues.at(kk) * 1000));
6110  if ( cxval == txval ) {
6111  rpidx = kk;
6112  xvals_pos[jj] = kk;
6113  break;
6114  }
6115  }
6116  if ( rpidx == -1 ) {
6117  xvals_pos[jj] = edata->pointCount();
6118  trx++;
6119  continue;
6120  }
6121 
6122  int idx_ii = ii * nwaveln * nscans;
6123  for ( int ss = 0; ss < nscans; ss++ )
6124  {
6125  double yval = edata->scanData.at(ss).rvalues.at(rpidx);
6126  int idx_ss = ss * nwaveln;
6127  int idx_wv = idx_ii + idx_ss + jj;
6128  yvals[idx_wv] = yval;
6129  }
6130 
6131  trx++;
6132  } // END: input triples loop
6133  }
6134  rdata << yvals;
6135  }
6136  DbgLv(1) << "IS-MWL: Triples loop complete";
6137 
6138  expc_radii.clear();
6139  expd_radii.clear();
6140  foreach (double xval, rdata_xvals.at(0)) {
6141  expc_radii << QString::number(xval);
6142  expd_radii << xval;
6143  }
6144 
6145 
6146 }

6230

6244  ct_to ->setMaximum( data.scanData.size() );

6273 // Handle a mouse click according to the current pick step
6274 void US_Edit::mouse( const QwtDoublePoint& p )
6275 {
6276  double maximum = -1.0e99;
6277 
6278  switch ( step )
6279  {
6280  case MENISCUS:
6281  if ( dataType == "IP" )
6282  {
6283  meniscus = p.x();
6284  // Un-zoom
6285  if ( plot->btnZoom->isChecked() )
6286  plot->btnZoom->setChecked( false );
6287 
6288  draw_vline( meniscus );
6289  }
6290 
6291  else if ( expIsEquil || men_1click )
6292  { // Equilibrium
6293 
6294  qDebug() << "Meniscus, expEquil OR men_1click ";
6295  meniscus_left = p.x();
6296  int ii = data.xindex( meniscus_left );
6297  draw_vline( meniscus_left );
6298  meniscus = data.radius( ii );
6299  range_left = meniscus + _RNGLEFT_OFFSET_;
6300  le_meniscus ->setText( QString::number( meniscus, 'f', 8 ) );
6301  le_dataStart->setText( QString::number( range_left, 'f', 8 ) );
6302 
6303  data_plot->replot();
6304 
6305  pb_meniscus->setIcon( check );
6306 
6307 // pb_dataRange->setEnabled( true );
6308 
6309  next_step();
6310  break;
6311  }
6312 
6313  else if ( meniscus_left == 0.0 )
6314  {
6315  meniscus_left = p.x();
6316  draw_vline( meniscus_left );
6317  break;
6318  }
6319  else
6320  {
6321  // Sometime we get two clicks
6322  if ( qAbs( p.x() - meniscus_left ) < 0.005 ) return;
6323 
6324  double meniscus_right = p.x();
6325 
6326  // Swap values if necessary. Use a macro in us_math.h
6327  if ( meniscus_right < meniscus_left )
6328  swap_double( meniscus_left, meniscus_right );
6329 
6330  // Find the radius for the max value
6331  maximum = -1.0e99;
6332  US_DataIO::Scan* s;
6333 
6334  for ( int i = 0; i < data.scanData.size(); i++ )
6335  {
6336  if ( ! includes.contains( i ) ) continue;
6337 
6338  s = &data.scanData[ i ];
6339  int start = data.xindex( meniscus_left );
6340  int end = data.xindex( meniscus_right );
6341 
6342  for ( int j = start; j <= end; j++ )
6343  {
6344  if ( maximum < s->rvalues[ j ] )
6345  {
6346  maximum = s->rvalues[ j ];
6347  meniscus = data.radius( j );
6348  }
6349  }
6350  }
6351 
6352  // Remove the left line
6353  if ( v_line != NULL )
6354  {
6355  v_line->detach();
6356  delete v_line;
6357  v_line = NULL;
6358  }
6359  }
6360 
6361  // Display the values
6362  range_left = meniscus + _RNGLEFT_OFFSET_;
6363  le_meniscus ->setText( QString::number( meniscus, 'f', 8 ) );
6364  le_dataStart->setText( QString::number( range_left, 'f', 8 ) );
6365 
6366  // Create a marker
6367  if ( dataType != "IP" )
6368  {
6369  marker = new QwtPlotMarker;
6370  QBrush brush( Qt::white );
6371  QPen pen ( brush, 2.0 );
6372  QwtSymbol * symb = new QwtSymbol( QwtSymbol::Cross,
6373  brush, pen, QSize ( 8, 8 ) );
6374  marker->setValue ( meniscus, maximum );
6375  marker->setSymbol( symb );
6376  marker->attach ( data_plot );
6377  }
6378 
6379  data_plot->replot();
6380 
6381  pb_meniscus->setIcon( check );
6382 
6383  if ( dataType == "IP" )
6384  {
6385  pb_airGap->setEnabled( true );
6386  set_airGap();
6387  }
6388  else
6389 // pb_dataRange->setEnabled( true );
6390 
6391  next_step();
6392  break;
6393 
6394  case AIRGAP:
6395  if ( airGap_left == 0.0 )
6396  {
6397  airGap_left = p.x();
6398  draw_vline( airGap_left );
6399  }
6400  else
6401  {
6402  // Sometime we get two clicks
6403  if ( qAbs( p.x() - airGap_left ) < 0.005 ) return;
6404 
6405  airGap_right = p.x();
6406 
6407  if ( airGap_right < airGap_left )
6408  swap_double( airGap_left, airGap_right );
6409 
6410  US_DataIO::EditValues edits;
6411  edits.airGapLeft = airGap_left;
6412  edits.airGapRight = airGap_right;
6413 
6414  QList< int > excludes;
6415 
6416  for ( int i = 0; i < data.scanData.size(); i++ )
6417  if ( ! includes.contains( i ) ) edits.excludes << i;
6418 
6419 DbgLv(1) << "AGap: L R" << airGap_left << airGap_right << " AdjIntf";
6420  US_DataIO::adjust_interference( data, edits );
6421 
6422  // Un-zoom
6423  if ( plot->btnZoom->isChecked() )
6424  plot->btnZoom->setChecked( false );
6425 
6426  // Display the data
6427  QString wkstr;
6428  le_airGap->setText( wkstr.sprintf( "%.3f - %.3f",
6429  airGap_left, airGap_right ) );
6430 
6431  step = RANGE;
6432  range_left = meniscus + _RNGLEFT_OFFSET_;
6433  le_dataStart->setText( QString::number( range_left, 'f', 8 ) );
6434 DbgLv(1) << "AGap: plot_range()";
6435 
6436  plot_range();
6437 
6438  qApp->processEvents();
6439 
6440  pb_airGap ->setIcon( check );
6441  pb_dataRange->setEnabled( true );
6442 
6443  next_step();
6444  }
6445 
6446  break;
6447 
6448 
6449 
6450  case RANGE:
6451  qDebug() << "range_left, range_right -- "
6452  << range_left << range_right;
6453  if ( range_left == 0.0 )
6454  {
6455  if ( v_line != NULL )
6456  {
6457  v_line->detach();
6458  delete v_line;
6459  v_line = NULL;
6460  }
6461 
6462  if ( p.x() <= meniscus )
6463  {
6464  le_dataRange->setText( tr( "**overlaps meniscus**" ) );
6465  break;
6466  }
6467 
6468  range_left = radius_indexed( p.x() );
6469  draw_vline( range_left );
6470  break;
6471  }
6472 
6473  else if ( range_right == 0.0 )
6474  {
6475  if ( v_line != NULL )
6476  {
6477  v_line->detach();
6478  delete v_line;
6479  v_line = NULL;
6480  }
6481 
6482  range_right = radius_indexed( p.x() );
6483 
6484  if ( ( range_right - meniscus ) < 0.4 )
6485  {
6486  range_right = 9.0;
6487  QMessageBox::critical( this,
6488  tr( "Range Right Error" ),
6489  tr( "The newest Edit does away with the need to\n"
6490  "select Range Left and Right or Plateau.\n"
6491  "Besides Meniscus, only Range Right need be\n"
6492  "selected by ctrl-click.\n\n"
6493  "Please ctrl-click to select the data end." ) );
6494 // qApp->processEvents();
6495  next_step();
6496  return;
6497  }
6498 
6499  draw_vline( range_right );
6500  le_dataEnd ->setText( QString::number( range_right, 'f', 8 ) );
6501  plateau = range_right - _PLATEAU_OFFSET_;
6502  le_plateau ->setText( QString::number( plateau, 'f', 8 ) );
6503 
6504 
6505  step = PLATEAU;
6506 
6507  plot_range();
6508 
6509  qApp->processEvents();
6510  break;
6511  }
6512 
6513  else
6514  {
6515  // Sometime we get two clicks
6516  if ( qAbs( p.x() - range_left ) < 0.020 ) return;
6517 
6518  range_right = radius_indexed( p.x() );
6519 
6520  if ( range_right < range_left )
6521  swap_double( range_left, range_right );
6522 
6523  if ( dataType == "IP" )
6524  {
6525  US_DataIO::EditValues edits;
6526  edits.rangeLeft = range_left;
6527  edits.rangeRight = range_right;
6528  edits.gapTolerance = ct_gaps->value();
6529

6531 
6532  for ( int i = 0; i < data.scanData.size(); i++ )
6533  if ( ! includes.contains( i ) ) edits.excludes << i;
6534 
6535  US_DataIO::calc_integral( data, edits );
6536  }
6537 
6538  // Display the data
6539  QString wkstr;
6540 // le_dataRange->setText( wkstr.sprintf( "%.3f - %.3f",
6541 // range_left, range_right ) );
6542  le_dataStart->setText( QString::number( range_left, 'f', 8 ) );
6543  le_dataEnd ->setText( QString::number( range_right, 'f', 8 ) );
6544  plateau = range_right - _PLATEAU_OFFSET_;
6545  le_plateau ->setText( QString::number( plateau, 'f', 3 ) );
6546 
6547  step = PLATEAU;
6548  plot_range();
6549  pb_report ->setEnabled( true );
6550 
6551  qApp->processEvents();
6552 
6553  // Skip the gap check for interference data
6554  if ( dataType != "IP" ) gap_check();
6555 
6556 // pb_dataRange->setIcon( check );
6557 // pb_plateau ->setEnabled( true );
6558  pb_dataEnd ->setIcon( check );
6559  pb_dataEnd ->setEnabled( true );
6560  pb_noise ->setEnabled( true );
6561  pb_spikes ->setEnabled( true );
6562 
6563  if ( us_edit_auto_mode || us_edit_auto_mode_manual || us_edit_auto_mode_manual_bll )
6564  pb_baseline_correct ->setEnabled( true );
6565 
6566  if ( ! expIsEquil )
6567  { // non-Equilibrium
6568 
6569  qDebug() << "In RANGES, nonEquilibrium, enabling next_step()";
6570  next_step();
6571  }
6572 
6573  else
6574  { // Equilibrium
6575 
6576  int index = cb_triple->currentIndex();
6577  int row = cb_rpms ->currentIndex();
6578  int jsd = sd_offs[ index ] + row;
6579  QString arpm = cb_rpms->itemText( row );
6580 
6581  if ( sData[ jsd ].meniscus == 0.0 &&
6582  meniscus > 0.0 )
6583  total_edits++;
6584 
6585  sData[ jsd ].meniscus = meniscus;
6586  sData[ jsd ].dataLeft = range_left;
6587  sData[ jsd ].dataRight = range_right;
6588 
6589  if ( ++row >= cb_rpms->count() )
6590  {
6591  if ( ++index < cb_triple->count() )
6592  {
6593  cb_triple->setCurrentIndex( index );
6594  step = MENISCUS;
6595  QString trsp =
6596  cb_triple->currentText() + " : " + trip_rpms[ 0 ];
6597  le_edtrsp->setText( trsp );
6598 
6599  data = *outData[ index ];
6600  cb_rpms->clear();
6601 
6602  for ( int ii = 0; ii < data.scanData.size(); ii++ )
6603  {
6604  QString arpm =
6605  QString::number( data.scanData[ ii ].rpm );
6606 
6607  if ( ! trip_rpms.contains( arpm ) )
6608  trip_rpms << arpm;
6609  }
6610 
6611  cb_rpms->addItems( trip_rpms );
6612  cb_rpms->setCurrentIndex( 0 );
6613 
6614  set_meniscus();
6615  }
6616 
6617  else
6618  {
6619  pb_report ->setEnabled( true );
6620  pb_write ->setEnabled( true );
6621 
6622  if ( us_edit_auto_mode_manual || us_edit_auto_mode_manual_bll )
6623  pb_pass->setEnabled( true );
6624 
6625  ck_writemwl->setEnabled( true );
6626  pb_reviewep->setEnabled( true );
6627  pb_nexteqtr->setEnabled( true );
6628  step = FINISHED;
6629  next_step();
6630 
6631  if ( total_edits >= total_speeds )
6632  review_edits();
6633  }
6634  }
6635 
6636  else
6637  {
6638  cb_rpms->setCurrentIndex( row );
6639  step = MENISCUS;
6640  QString trsp =
6641  cb_triple->currentText() + " : " + trip_rpms[ row ];
6642  le_edtrsp->setText( trsp );
6643 
6644  set_meniscus();
6645  }
6646  }
6647 
6648  if ( total_edits >= total_speeds )
6649  {
6650  qDebug() << "In RANGES: total_edits, total_speeds: " << total_edits << ", " << total_speeds;
6651  all_edits = true;
6652  pb_write ->setEnabled( true );
6653 
6654  if ( us_edit_auto_mode_manual || us_edit_auto_mode_manual_bll )
6655  pb_pass->setEnabled( true );
6656 
6657  ck_writemwl->setEnabled( true );
6658  changes_made = all_edits;
6659  }
6660  }
6661 
6662  break;
6663 
6664  case PLATEAU:
6665 
6666 #if 0
6667  if ( p.x() > range_right )
6668  {
6669  le_plateau->setText( tr( "**beyond data end**" ) );
6670  break;
6671  }
6672 
6673  plateau = radius_indexed( p.x() );
6674 #endif
6675  plateau = range_right - _PLATEAU_OFFSET_;
6676 
6677  // Display the data (localize str)
6678  le_plateau ->setText( QString::number( plateau, 'f', 8 ) );
6679 
6680  plot_range();
6681  pb_plateau ->setIcon( check );
6682  ct_to->setValue( 0.0 ); // Uncolor all scans
6683  pb_report ->setEnabled( true );
6684  pb_write ->setEnabled( true );
6685 
6686  if ( us_edit_auto_mode_manual || us_edit_auto_mode_manual_bll )
6687  pb_pass->setEnabled( true );
6688 
6689  ck_writemwl->setEnabled( isMwl );
6690  changes_made = true;
6691  next_step();
6692  break;
6693 
6694  case BASELINE:
6695  {
6696  // Use the last scan
6697  US_DataIO::Scan* scan = &data.scanData.last();
6698 
6699  int start = data.xindex( range_left );
6700  int end = data.xindex( range_right );
6701  int pt = data.xindex( p.x() );
6702 
6703  if ( pt - start < 5 || end - pt < 5 )
6704  {
6705  QMessageBox::warning( this,
6706  tr( "Position Error" ),
6707  tr( "The selected point is too close to the edge." ) );
6708  return;
6709  }
6710 
6711  double sum = 0.0;
6712 
6713  // Average the value for +/- 5 points
6714  for ( int j = pt - 5; j <= pt + 5; j++ )
6715  sum += scan->rvalues[ j ];
6716 
6717  double bl = sum / 11.0;
6718  baseline = p.x();
6719  plateau = ( plateau > 0.0 ) ? plateau
6720  : ( range_right - _PLATEAU_OFFSET_ );
6721 
6722  QString wkstr;
6723  le_baseline->setText( wkstr.sprintf( "%.3f (%.3e)", baseline, bl ) );
6724 DbgLv(1) << "BL: AA : baseline bl" << baseline << bl;
6725  le_plateau ->setText( QString::number( plateau, 'f', 8 ) );
6726  plot_range();
6727  }
6728 
6729  pb_report ->setEnabled( true );
6730  pb_write ->setEnabled( true );
6731 
6732  if ( us_edit_auto_mode_manual || us_edit_auto_mode_manual_bll )
6733  pb_pass->setEnabled( true );
6734 
6735  ck_writemwl ->setEnabled( isMwl );
6736  changes_made = true;
6737  next_step();
6738  break;
6739 
6740  case BASELINE_LINEAR_CORR:
6741  qDebug() << "bl_corr_left, bl_corr_right {xx,yy} -- "
6742  << bl_corr_left_x << bl_corr_right_x
6743  << bl_corr_left_y << bl_corr_right_y;
6744  if ( bl_corr_left_x == 0.0 )
6745  {
6746  bl_corr_left_x = radius_indexed( p.x() );
6747  bl_corr_left_y = p.y();
6748 
6749  qDebug() << "[FIRST]bl_corr_left, bl_corr_right {xx,yy} -- "
6750  << bl_corr_left_x << bl_corr_right_x
6751  << bl_corr_left_y << bl_corr_right_y;
6752 
6753  fixedPoint = QPointF(p.x(),p.y());
6754  qDebug() << "fixedPoint -- "
6755  << fixedPoint.x()
6756  << fixedPoint.y();
6757 
6758  pick->setStateMachine(new QwtPickerTrackerMachine());
6759  connect(pick, SIGNAL(moved(const QPointF&)), this, SLOT(onMouseMoved(const QPointF&)));
6760 
6761  break;
6762  }
6763  else
6764  {
6765  disconnect(pick, SIGNAL(moved(const QPointF&)), 0, 0);
6766  if ( line_to_mouse != NULL )
6767  {
6768  line_to_mouse->detach();
6769  delete line_to_mouse;
6770  line_to_mouse = NULL;
6771  }
6772 
6773  bl_corr_right_x = radius_indexed( p.x() );
6774  bl_corr_right_y = p.y();
6775 
6776  qDebug() << "[SECOND]bl_corr_left, bl_corr_right {xx,yy} -- "
6777  << bl_corr_left_x << bl_corr_right_x
6778  << bl_corr_left_y << bl_corr_right_y;
6779  }
6780 
6781  {
6782  bl_corr_slope = (bl_corr_right_y - bl_corr_left_y) / ( bl_corr_right_x - bl_corr_left_x);
6783  double x_intercept = bl_corr_left_x - bl_corr_left_y / bl_corr_slope;
6784  bl_corr_yintercept = bl_corr_left_y - bl_corr_slope*bl_corr_left_x;
6785 
6786  //replot with baseline corrections
6787  plot_range_and_blc();
6788 
6789  //enable accept
6790  if ( us_edit_auto_mode_manual || us_edit_auto_mode_manual_bll )
6791  pb_pass->setEnabled( true );
6792 
6793  //update gui fields
6794  le_bll_slope ->setText( QString::number( bl_corr_slope, 'f', 8 ) );
6795  le_bll_intercept ->setText( QString::number( bl_corr_yintercept, 'f', 8 ) );
6796  }
6797  break;
6798 
6799  default:
6800  break;
6801  }
6802 }

6804 void US_Edit::onMouseMoved(const QPointF& mousePos)
6805 {
6806  // Remove the left line
6807  if ( line_to_mouse != NULL )
6808  {
6809  line_to_mouse->detach();
6810  delete line_to_mouse;
6811  line_to_mouse = NULL;
6812  }
6813 
6814  #if QT_VERSION < 0x050000
6815  QwtScaleDiv* y_axis = data_plot->axisScaleDiv( QwtPlot::yLeft );
6816 #else
6817  QwtScaleDiv* y_axis = (QwtScaleDiv*)&data_plot->axisScaleDiv( QwtPlot::yLeft );
6818 #endif
6819 
6820  QVector<double> x, y;
6821  x.push_back(fixedPoint.x());
6822  y.push_back(fixedPoint.y());
6823  x.push_back(mousePos.x());
6824  y.push_back(mousePos.y());
6825  line_to_mouse = us_curve( data_plot, "Line-to-Mouse" );
6826  line_to_mouse->setSamples(x, y);
6827  QPen pen = QPen( QBrush( Qt::red ), 2.0 );
6828  line_to_mouse->setPen( pen );
6829  data_plot->replot();
6830 
6831 }

6862 // Set the step flag for the next step
6863 void US_Edit::next_step( void )
6864 {
6865  QPushButton* pb;
6866 
6867  if ( meniscus == 0.0 )
6868  {
6869  step = MENISCUS;
6870  pb = pb_meniscus;
6871  }
6872 
6873  else if ( airGap_right == 9.0 && dataType == "IP" )
6874  {
6875  step = AIRGAP;
6876  pb = pb_airGap;
6877  set_airGap();
6878  }
6879 
6880  else if ( range_right == 9.0 )
6881  {
6882  step = RANGE;
6883 // pb = pb_dataRange;
6884  pb = pb_dataEnd;
6885  }
6886 
6887 #if 0
6888  else if ( plateau == 0.0 )
6889  {
6890  step = PLATEAU;
6891  pb = pb_plateau;
6892  }
6893 #endif
6894 
6895  else
6896  { // All values up to Plateau have been entered: Finished
6897  step = FINISHED;
6898  pb = NULL;
6899 // pb = pb_dataEnd;
6900  double sum = 0.0;
6901  int pt = data.xindex( range_left );
6902  baseline = data.xvalues[ pt + 5 ];
6903  plateau = ( plateau > 0.0 ) ? plateau
6904  : ( range_right - _PLATEAU_OFFSET_ );
6905 
6906  if ( !isMwl )
6907  {
6908  // Average the value for +/- 5 points
6909  for ( int jj = pt; jj < pt + 11; jj++ )
6910  sum += data.scanData.last().rvalues[ jj ];
6911 
6912  double bl = sum / 11.0;
6913 
6914  QString str;
6915  le_baseline->setText( str.sprintf( "%.3f (%.3e)", baseline, bl ) );
6916  DbgLv(1) << "BL: BB : baseline bl" << baseline << bl;
6917 
6918  baseline_od = bl;
6919 
6920  qDebug() << "SETTING Baseline, Plateau : baseline bl" << baseline << bl;
6921  le_plateau ->setText( QString::number( plateau, 'f', 8 ) );
6922  }
6923  else
6924  {
6925  if ( us_edit_auto_mode )
6926  {
6927  plateau = range_right - _PLATEAU_OFFSET_;
6928  le_plateau ->setText( QString::number( plateau, 'f', 3 ) );
6929 
6930  le_baseline ->setText( QString::number( baseline, 'f', 3 ) );
6931 
6932  baseline_od = 0;
6933  }
6934  }
6935 
6936  }
6937 
6938  set_pbColors( pb );
6939 }

7134 // Set up for a Fringe Tolerance pick
7135 void US_Edit::set_fringe_tolerance( double ftvalue )
7136 {
7137 DbgLv(1) << " gap_fringe" << gap_fringe << "SFT: dataType" << dataType << "ftvalue" << ftvalue;
7138  // This is only valid for interference data
7139  if ( dataType != "IP" ) return;
7140 
7141  gap_fringe = ftvalue;
7142 DbgLv(1) << " 1)gap_fringe" << gap_fringe;
7143 
7144  // If we haven't yet set the range, just ignore the change
7145  if ( step == MENISCUS || step == AIRGAP || step == RANGE ) return;
7146 
7147  // Reset the data
7148  int index = index_data();
7149  data = *outData[ index ];
7150 
7151  US_DataIO::EditValues edits;
7152  edits.airGapLeft = airGap_left;
7153  edits.airGapRight = airGap_right;
7154 
7155  QList< int > excludes;
7156 
7157  for ( int i = 0; i < data.scanData.size(); i++ )
7158  if ( ! includes.contains( i ) ) edits.excludes << i;
7159 
7160  US_DataIO::adjust_interference( data, edits );
7161 
7162  edits.rangeLeft = range_left;
7163  edits.rangeRight = range_right;
7164  edits.gapTolerance = ct_gaps->value();
7165 DbgLv(1) << " 3)gap_fringe" << gap_fringe << "index" << index;
7166 
7167  US_DataIO::calc_integral( data, edits );
7168  replot();
7169 }
7170 
7171 // Plot all curves
7172 void US_Edit::plot_all( void )
7173 {
7174  if ( isMwl )
7175  {
7176  plot_mwl();
7177  return;
7178  }
7179  QList< QColor > mcolors;
7180  int nmcols = plot->map_colors( mcolors );
7181 DbgLv(1) << " PlAll: nmcols" << nmcols;
7182  QPen pen_plot( US_GuiSettings::plotCurve() );
7183  if ( nmcols == 1 )
7184  pen_plot = QPen( mcolors[ 0 ] );
7185 
7186  if ( plot->btnZoom->isChecked() )
7187  plot->btnZoom->setChecked( false );
7188 
7189  data_plot->detachItems( QwtPlotItem::Rtti_PlotCurve );
7190  v_line = NULL;
7191 
7192  int size = data.pointCount();
7193 
7194  QVector< double > rvec( size );
7195  QVector< double > vvec( size );
7196  double* r = rvec.data();
7197  double* v = vvec.data();
7198 
7199  double maxR = -1.0e99;
7200  double minR = 1.0e99;
7201  double maxV = -1.0e99;
7202  double minV = 1.0e99;
7203 
7204  for ( int i = 0; i < data.scanData.size(); i++ )
7205  {
7206  if ( ! includes.contains( i ) ) continue;
7207 
7208  US_DataIO::Scan* s = &data.scanData[ i ];
7209 
7210  for ( int j = 0; j < size; j++ )
7211  {
7212  r[ j ] = data.xvalues[ j ];
7213  v[ j ] = s ->rvalues[ j ] * invert;
7214 
7215  maxR = qMax( maxR, r[ j ] );
7216  minR = qMin( minR, r[ j ] );
7217  maxV = qMax( maxV, v[ j ] );
7218  minV = qMin( minV, v[ j ] );
7219  }
7220 
7221  QString title = tr( "Raw Data at " )
7222  + QString::number( s->seconds ) + tr( " seconds" )
7223  + " #" + QString::number( i );
7224 
7225  QwtPlotCurve* c = us_curve( data_plot, title );
7226  c->setPaintAttribute( QwtPlotCurve::ClipPolygons, true );
7227  if ( nmcols > 1 )
7228  {
7229  pen_plot = QPen( mcolors[ i % nmcols ] );
7230 DbgLv(2) << " PlAll: i" << i << "pen_plot" << pen_plot;
7231  }
7232  c->setPen ( pen_plot );
7233 
7234  c->setSamples( r, v, size );
7235  }
7236 
7237  // Reset the scan curves within the new limits
7238  double padR = ( maxR - minR ) / 30.0;
7239  double padV = ( maxV - minV ) / 30.0;
7240 
7241  data_plot->setAxisScale( QwtPlot::yLeft , minV - padV, maxV + padV );
7242  data_plot->setAxisScale( QwtPlot::xBottom, minR - padR, maxR + padR );
7243 
7244  // Reset colors
7245  focus( (int)ct_from->value(), (int)ct_to->value() );
7246  data_plot->replot();
7247 }
7248 
7249 // Plot curves with linear baseline corrections
7250 void US_Edit::plot_range_and_blc( void )
7251 {
7252  if ( plot->btnZoom->isChecked() )
7253  plot->btnZoom->setChecked( false );
7254 
7255  QList< QColor > mcolors;
7256  int nmcols = plot->map_colors( mcolors );
7257 DbgLv(1) << " PlRng: nmcols" << nmcols;
7258  QPen pen_plot( US_GuiSettings::plotCurve() );
7259  if ( nmcols == 1 )
7260  pen_plot = QPen( mcolors[ 0 ] );
7261  data_plot->detachItems( QwtPlotItem::Rtti_PlotCurve );
7262 
7263  int rsize = data.pointCount();
7264  QVector< double > rvec( rsize );
7265  QVector< double > vvec( rsize );
7266  double* r = rvec.data();
7267  double* v = vvec.data();
7268  double maxR = -1.0e99;
7269  double minR = 1.0e99;
7270  double maxV = -1.0e99;
7271  double minV = 1.0e99;
7272  int indext = cb_triple->currentIndex();
7273 
7274  if ( isMwl )
7275  {
7276  //if ( !us_edit_auto_mode )
7277  //{
7278  int ccx = indext;
7279  int wvx = cb_lplot->currentIndex();
7280  indext = ccx * nwaveln + wvx;
7281 DbgLv(1) << "plot_range(): ccx wvx indext" << ccx << wvx << indext;
7282  //}
7283  }
7284 
7285  // For each scan
7286  for ( int i = 0; i < data.scanData.size(); i++ )
7287  {
7288  if ( ! includes.contains( i ) ) continue;
7289 
7290  US_DataIO::Scan* s = &data.scanData[ i ];
7291 
7292  int indexLeft = data.xindex( range_left );
7293  int indexRight = data.xindex( range_right );
7294  double menp = 0.0;
7295 
7296  if ( expIsEquil )
7297  {
7298  double rngl = range_left;
7299  double rngr = range_right;
7300  int tScan = i + 1;
7301  int jsd = sd_offs[ indext ];
7302  int ksd = jsd + sd_knts[ indext ];
7303 
7304  for ( int jj = jsd; jj < ksd; jj++ )
7305  {
7306  int sScan = sData[ jj ].first_scan;
7307  int eScan = sData[ jj ].scan_count + sScan - 1;
7308 
7309  if ( tScan < sScan || tScan > eScan )
7310  continue;
7311 
7312  rngl = sData[ jj ].dataLeft;
7313  rngr = sData[ jj ].dataRight;
7314  menp = sData[ jj ].meniscus;
7315  break;
7316  }
7317 
7318  indexLeft = data.xindex( rngl );
7319  indexRight = data.xindex( rngr );
7320 
7321  int inxm = data.xindex( menp );
7322 
7323  if ( inxm < 1 )
7324  return;
7325 
7326  r[ 0 ] = data.xvalues[ inxm ];
7327  v[ 0 ] = s ->rvalues[ indexLeft ];
7328  r[ 2 ] = data.xvalues[ inxm + 2 ];
7329  v[ 2 ] = s ->rvalues[ indexLeft + 4 ];
7330  r[ 1 ] = r[ 0 ];
7331  v[ 1 ] = v[ 2 ];
7332  r[ 3 ] = r[ 2 ];
7333  v[ 3 ] = v[ 0 ];
7334  r[ 4 ] = r[ 0 ];
7335  v[ 4 ] = v[ 0 ];
7336 
7337  QwtPlotCurve* c = us_curve( data_plot, tr( "Meniscus at" ) +
7338  QString::number( tScan ) );
7339  c->setBrush( QBrush( Qt::cyan ) );
7340  c->setPen( QPen( Qt::cyan ) );
7341  c->setSamples( r, v, 5 );
7342  minR = qMin( minR, r[ 0 ] );
7343  minV = qMin( minV, v[ 0 ] );
7344  }
7345 
7346  int count = 0;
7347 
7348  for ( int j = indexLeft; j <= indexRight; j++ )
7349  {
7350  r[ count ] = data.xvalues[ j ];
7351  //v[ count ] = s ->rvalues[ j ] * invert;
7352  v[ count ] = s ->rvalues[ j ] * invert - ( r[ count ]*bl_corr_slope + bl_corr_yintercept);
7353 
7354  maxR = qMax( maxR, r[ count ] );
7355  minR = qMin( minR, r[ count ] );
7356  maxV = qMax( maxV, v[ count ] );
7357  minV = qMin( minV, v[ count ] );
7358 
7359  count++;
7360  }
7361 
7362  QString title = tr( "Raw Data at " )
7363  + QString::number( s->seconds ) + tr( " seconds" )
7364  + " #" + QString::number( i );
7365 
7366  QwtPlotCurve* c = us_curve( data_plot, title );
7367  if ( nmcols > 1 )
7368  {
7369  pen_plot = QPen( mcolors[ i % nmcols ] );
7370 DbgLv(2) << " PlRng: i" << i << "pen_plot" << pen_plot;
7371  }
7372  c->setPen ( pen_plot );
7373  c->setSamples( r, v, count );
7374  }
7375 
7376  // Reset the scan curves within the new limits
7377  double padR = ( maxR - minR ) / 30.0;
7378  double padV = ( maxV - minV ) / 30.0;
7379 
7380  data_plot->setAxisScale( QwtPlot::yLeft , minV - padV, maxV + padV );
7381  data_plot->setAxisScale( QwtPlot::xBottom, minR - padR, maxR + padR );
7382 
7383  // Reset colors
7384  focus( (int)ct_from->value(), (int)ct_to->value() );
7385  data_plot->replot();
7386 
7387 
7388 }

7807  for ( int ii = 0; ii < nscan; ii++ )
7808  {

7810  {

7812  continue;

7816  int kk = ptxs;
7817 
7818  for ( int jj = 0; jj < npoint; jj++ )
7819  {
7820  rr[ jj ] = data.xvalues[ jj ];
7821  valueV = qMin( maxOD, scn->rvalues[ kk++ ] * invert );
7822  vv[ jj ] = valueV;
7823 
7824  maxR = qMax( maxR, rr[ jj ] );
7825  minR = qMin( minR, rr[ jj ] );
7826  maxV = qMax( maxV, valueV );

7828

7830  kodlim++;
7831  }

7835  + " #" + QString::number( ii );

7838  cc->setPaintAttribute( QwtPlotCurve::ClipPolygons, true );
7839  cc->setSamples( rr, vv, npoint );
7840  }
7841  pick ->disconnect();

7843  SLOT ( mouse ( const QwtDoublePoint& ) ) );
7844 DbgLv(1) << "PlMwl: END xa_RAD kodlim odlimit" << kodlim << odlimit;
7845  }
7846 
7847  else
7848  { // Build plot of radius record with wavelength points
7849 DbgLv(1) << "PlMwl: START xa_WAV";
7850  data_plot->setAxisTitle( QwtPlot::xBottom, tr( "Wavelength (nm)" ) );
7851  int ccx = cb_triple->currentIndex();

7855  rvec << rwvl;
7856  minR = qMin(minR, static_cast<double>(rwvl));
7857  maxR = qMax(maxR, static_cast<double>(rwvl));
7858  }

7870  int idx = idx_ii + idx_ss + jj;
7871  double val = vvcec_all.at(idx);
7872  maxV = qMax( maxV, val );
7873  minV = qMin( minV, val );
7874  vvec << val;
7875  }
7876  vv = vvec.data();
7877  QwtPlotCurve* cc = us_curve( data_plot, tr("Scan %1").arg(ss) );
7878  cc->setPaintAttribute( QwtPlotCurve::ClipPolygons, true );
7879  cc->setSamples( rr, vv, nwaveln );
7880  }
7881  }
7882 
7883  // Reset the scan curves within the new limits
7884  double padR = ( maxR - minR ) / 30.0;
7885  double padV = ( maxV - minV ) / 30.0;
7886  padV = qMax( padV, 0.005 );
7887 
7888  data_plot->setAxisScale( QwtPlot::yLeft , minV - padV, maxV + padV );

7945 // Set focus From/To
7946 void US_Edit::focus( int from, int to )
7947 {
7948  if ( from == 0 )
7949  pb_edit1 ->setEnabled( false );
7950  else
7951  pb_edit1 ->setEnabled( true );
7952 
7953  if ( to == 0 )
7954  pb_excludeRange->setEnabled( false );
7955  else
7956  pb_excludeRange->setEnabled( true );
7957 
7958  QList< int > focus;
7959  int ifrom = qMax( from - 1, 0 );
7960  int ito = qMin( to, includes.size() );
7961 
7962  for ( int ii = ifrom; ii < ito; ii++ )
7963  focus << includes.at( ii );
7964 
7965  set_colors( focus );
7966 }

7968 // Set curve colors
7969 void US_Edit::set_colors( const QList< int >& focus )
7970 {
7971  QList< QColor > mcolors;
7972  int nmcols = plot->map_colors( mcolors );
7973 DbgLv(1) << "ED:scol: nmcols" << nmcols << mcolors.size();
7974  QPen pen_plot( US_GuiSettings::plotCurve() );
7975  if ( nmcols == 1 )
7976  pen_plot = QPen( mcolors[ 0 ] );
7977 
7978  // Get pointers to curves
7979  QwtPlotItemList list = data_plot->itemList();
7980  QList< QwtPlotCurve* > curves;
7981 
7982  for ( int i = 0; i < list.size(); i++ )
7983  {
7984  if ( list[ i ]->title().text().contains( "Raw" ) )
7985  curves << dynamic_cast< QwtPlotCurve* >( list[ i ] );
7986  }
7987 
7988  QPen p = curves[ 0 ]->pen();
7989  QBrush b = curves[ 0 ]->brush();
7990  QColor foc = Qt::red;
7991 
7992  // Mark these scans in red
7993  for ( int i = 0; i < curves.size(); i++ )
7994  {
7995  int scnnbr = curves[ i ]->title().text().section( "#", 1, 1 ).toInt();
7996 
7997  if ( focus.contains( scnnbr ) )
7998  {
7999  p.setColor( foc );
8000  b.setColor( foc );
8001 
8002  curves[ i ]->setPen ( p );
8003  curves[ i ]->setBrush( b );
8004  }
8005  else if ( scnnbr > 0 )
8006  {
8007  scnnbr--;
8008 //DbgLv(1) << "ED:scol: i" << i << "scnx" << scnnbr;
8009  if ( nmcols > 1 )
8010  pen_plot = QPen( mcolors[ scnnbr % nmcols ] );
8011  curves[ i ]->setPen( pen_plot );
8012  }
8013  }
8014 
8015  data_plot->replot();
8016 }

8137 // Update scan points
8138 void US_Edit::update_scan( QList< QPointF > changes )
8139 {
8140  // Handle excluded scans
8141  int index1 = (int)ct_from->value();
8142  int current_scan = includes[ index1 - 1 ];
8143  US_DataIO::Scan* s = &data.scanData[ current_scan ];
8144 
8145  for ( int i = 0; i < changes.size(); i++ )
8146  {
8147  int point = (int)changes[ i ].x();
8148  double value = changes[ i ].y();
8149 
8150  s->rvalues[ point ] = value;
8151  }
8152 
8153  // Save changes for writing output
8154  Edits e;
8155  e.scan = current_scan;
8156  e.changes = changes;
8157  changed_points << e;
8158 
8159  // Set data for the curve
8160  int points = data.pointCount();
8161  QVector< double > rvec( points );
8162  QVector< double > vvec( points );
8163  double* r = rvec.data();
8164  double* v = vvec.data();
8165 
8166  int left;
8167  int right;
8168  int count = 0;
8169 
8170  if ( range_left > 0 )
8171  {
8172  left = data.xindex( range_left );
8173  right = data.xindex( range_right );
8174  }
8175  else
8176  {
8177  left = 0;
8178  right = points - 1;
8179  }
8180 
8181  for ( int i = left; i <= right; i++ )
8182  {
8183  r[ count ] = data.xvalues[ i ];
8184  v[ count ] = s ->rvalues[ i ];
8185  count++;
8186  }
8187 
8188  // Find the pointer to the current scan
8189  QwtPlotItemList items = data_plot->itemList();
8190  QString seconds = " " + QString::number( s->seconds );
8191  bool found = false;
8192 
8193  QwtPlotCurve* c;
8194  for ( int i = 0; i < items.size(); i++ )
8195  {
8196  if ( items[ i ]->rtti() == QwtPlotItem::Rtti_PlotCurve )
8197  {
8198  c = dynamic_cast< QwtPlotCurve* >( items[ i ] );
8199  if ( c->title().text().contains( seconds ) )
8200  {
8201  found = true;
8202  break;
8203  }
8204  }
8205  }
8206 
8207  if ( found )
8208  {
8209  // Update the curve
8210  c->setSamples( r, v, count );
8211  data_plot->replot();
8212  }
8213  else
8214  qDebug() << "Can't find curve!";
8215 
8216 }
8217

8222  reset_excludes();
8223 }

8242 // Remove spikes
8243 void US_Edit::remove_spikes( void )
8244 {
8245  double smoothed_value;
8246 
8247  // For each scan
8248  for ( int i = 0; i < data.scanData.size(); i++ )
8249  {
8250  US_DataIO::Scan* s = &data.scanData [ i ];
8251 
8252  int start = data.xindex( range_left );
8253  int end = data.xindex( range_right );
8254 
8255  for ( int j = start; j < end; j++ )
8256  {
8257  if ( US_DataIO::spike_check( *s, data.xvalues, j, start, end,
8258  &smoothed_value ) )
8259  {
8260  s->rvalues[ j ] = smoothed_value;
8261 
8262  // If previous consecututive points are interpolated, then
8263  // redo them
8264  int index = j - 1;
8265  unsigned char c = s->interpolated[ index / 8 ];
8266 
8267  while ( c & ( 1 << ( 7 - index % 8 ) ) )
8268  {
8269  if ( US_DataIO::spike_check( *s, data.xvalues,
8270  index, start, end, &smoothed_value ) )
8271  s->rvalues[ index ] = smoothed_value;
8272 
8273  index--;
8274  c = s->interpolated[ index / 8 ];
8275  }
8276  }
8277  }
8278  }
8279 
8280  pb_spikes->setIcon ( check );
8281  pb_spikes->setEnabled( false );
8282  pb_write ->setEnabled( true );
8283  replot();
8284 
8285 
8286 }
8287

8559  edits.gapTolerance = ct_gaps->value();
8560 
8561  for ( int i = 0; i < data.scanData.size(); i++ )
8562  if ( ! includes.contains( i ) ) edits.excludes << i;
8563 
8564  if ( step > AIRGAP )
8565  US_DataIO::adjust_interference( data, edits );
8566 
8567  if ( step > RANGE )
8568  US_DataIO::calc_integral( data, edits );
8569  }
8570 
8571  replot();
8572 
8573  // Reset buttons and structures
8574  pb_residuals->setEnabled( false );
8575 
8576  if ( step < PLATEAU )
8577  {
8578  pb_noise ->setEnabled( false );
8579  pb_spikes->setEnabled( false );
8580  }
8581  else
8582  {
8583  pb_noise ->setEnabled( true );
8584  pb_spikes->setEnabled( true );
8585  }
8586 
8587  spikes = false;
8588  noise_order = 0;
8589 
8590  // Remove icons
8591  pb_noise ->setIcon( QIcon() );
8592  pb_residuals ->setIcon( QIcon() );
8593  pb_spikes ->setIcon( QIcon() );
8594 }
8595 
8596 // Calculate and apply noise
8597 void US_Edit::noise( void )
8598 {
8599  residuals.clear();
8600  US_RiNoise* dialog = new US_RiNoise( data, includes,
8601  range_left, range_right, dataType, noise_order, residuals );
8602  int code = dialog->exec();
8603  qApp->processEvents();
8604 
8605  if ( code == QDialog::Accepted )
8606  {
8607  pb_noise ->setIcon( check );
8608  pb_residuals->setEnabled( true );
8609  }
8610  else
8611  pb_residuals->setEnabled( false );
8612 
8613  delete dialog;
8614 }
8615 
8616 // Subtract residuals
8617 void US_Edit::subtract_residuals( void )
8618 {
8619  for ( int i = 0; i < data.scanCount(); i++ )
8620  {
8621  for ( int j = 0; j < data.pointCount(); j++ )
8622  data.scanData[ i ].rvalues[ j ] -= residuals[ i ];
8623  }
8624 
8625  pb_residuals->setEnabled( false );
8626  pb_residuals->setIcon ( check );
8627  replot();
8628 }

9421 // Save edit profile(s)
9422 void US_Edit::write( void )
9423 {

9425  US_DB2* dbP = NULL;
9426 
9427  if ( disk_controls->db() )
9428  {
9429  US_Passwd pw;
9430  dbP = new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() );
9431 
9432  if ( dbP->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
9433  {
9434  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Connection Problem" ),
9435  tr( "Could not connect to database: \n" ) + dbP->lastError() );
9436  return;
9437  }
9438  }
9439 
9440  // Compute and store the post-stream bottom value
9441  US_SimulationParameters simparams;
9442  simparams.initFromData( dbP, data, false, runID, dataType );
9443  bottom = simparams.bottom;
9444 //*DEBUG*
9445 //bottom+=0.001;
9446 //*DEBUG*
9447 DbgLv(1) << "ED: Wr : bottom" << bottom;
9448 
9449  if ( !expIsEquil )
9450  { // non-Equilibrium: write single current edit (if "all" unchecked)
9451  if ( isMwl && ck_writemwl->isChecked() )
9452  { // Write edits for all triples in the current cell/channel
9453  write_mwl();
9454  }
9455 
9456  else
9457  { // Write single triple's edit
9458  triple_index = cb_triple->currentIndex();
9459 
9460  write_triple();
9461  }
9462  }
9463 
9464  else
9465  { // Equilibrium: loop to write all edits
9466  for ( int jr = 0; jr < triples.size(); jr++ )
9467  {
9468  triple_index = jr;
9469  data = *outData[ jr ];
9470 
9471  write_triple();
9472  }
9473  }
9474 
9475  changes_made = false;
9476  pb_write ->setEnabled( false );
9477  ck_writemwl ->setEnabled( false );
9478  pb_nextChan ->setEnabled( triples.size() > 1 && cb_triple->currentIndex() < triples.size()-1 );
9479 }

9572 QMap< QString, QString> US_Edit::read_autoflow_record( int autoflowID )
9573 {

9575  US_Passwd pw;

9578 
9579  QMap <QString, QString> protocol_details;
9580

9583  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Connection Problem" ),

9607  protocol_details[ "OptimaName" ] = db->value( 9 ).toString();
9608  protocol_details[ "runStarted" ] = db->value( 10 ).toString();
9609  protocol_details[ "invID_passed" ] = db->value( 11 ).toString();
9610 
9611  protocol_details[ "correctRadii" ] = db->value( 13 ).toString();

10356  json_status = compose_json( false );
10357  qDebug() << "isSet_to_edit_triple() FALSE: " << triples_all_optics[j] << json_status;
10358 
10359  ID = create_autoflowAnalysis_record( dbP, triples_all_optics[j], json_status );
10360  }
10361  }
10362  //No informaiton on specifi triple to edit -- select 1st triple in a channel as default
10363  else
10364  {
10365  json_status = compose_json( true );
10366  qDebug() << "isSet_edit_info_for_channel() FALSE: " << triples_all_optics[j] << json_status;
10367 
10368  ID = create_autoflowAnalysis_record( dbP, triples_all_optics[j], json_status );
10369 
10370  //So, reference wvl is defiend as the 1st one in the channel domain
10371  isSet_ref_wvl[ channels_all[i] ] = true;
10372 
10373  if (ID)
10374  create_autoflowAnalysisStages_record( dbP, ID );
10375  }
10376  }
10377  else
10378  {
10379  json_status = compose_json( false );
10380  qDebug() << triples_all_optics[j] << json_status;
10381 
10382  ID = create_autoflowAnalysis_record( dbP, triples_all_optics[j], json_status );
10383  }
10384  }
10385  }
10386 
10387  if ( ID )
10388  AnalysisIDs << QString::number( ID );
10389 
10390  }
10391  }
10392  }
10393 
10394 
10395  le_status->setText( tr( "Saving COMPLETE " ) );
10396  qApp->processEvents();
10397 
10398  //If AnalysisIDs empty, STOP here and return: Nothing to process further; emit signal to reset
10399  if ( AnalysisIDs.isEmpty() )
10400  {
10401  qDebug() << "Nothing to Analyse!!!";
10402  QMessageBox::information( this,
10403  tr( "Saving of Edit Profiles is Complete." ),
10404  tr( "Edit profiles were saved successfully. \n\n"
10405  "No triples were set for analysis. Program will be reset." ) );
10406  reset();
10407  //delete_autoflow_record();
10408  emit back_to_initAutoflow( );
10409  return;
10410  }
10411 
10412  // Otherwise, proceed to analysis: Now we need to Update autoflow record, reset GUI && send signal to switch to Analysis stage:
10413  QString AnalysisIDsString = AnalysisIDs.join(",");
10414  update_autoflow_record_atEditData( dbP, AnalysisIDsString );
10415 
10416  //Pass analsyisIDs generated to details_at_editing_local
10417  details_at_editing_local[ "analysisIDs" ] = AnalysisIDsString;
10418 
10419  //ALEXEY: here major actions on setting analysis tables etc. !!!!
10420  QMessageBox::information( this,
10421  tr( "Saving of Edit Profiles is Complete." ),
10422  tr( "Edit profiles were saved successfully. \n\n"
10423  "The program will switch to Analysis stage." ) );
10424  reset();
10425  this->close();
10426  qApp->processEvents();
10427 
10428  emit edit_complete_auto( details_at_editing_local );
10429 }

10595 bool US_Edit::isSet_to_analyse( QString triple_name, QString opsys )
10596 {
10597  bool have_run = false;
10598 
10599  //In case anaprofile does not have "run" attr, so QMap<> channels_to_analyse empty (older protocols):
10600  if ( channels_to_analyse.isEmpty() )
10601  {
10602  qDebug() << "It looks like older protocol is in use: QMap channels_to_analyse is EMPTY!";
10603 
10604  have_run = true;
10605  return have_run;
10606  }
10607 
10608  QStringList triple_name_list = triple_name.split(".");
10609  QString channel = triple_name_list[0] + triple_name_list[1];
10610 
10611  qDebug() << "[isSet_to_analyse()] channel1 -- " << channel;
10612  if ( dataSource. contains("DiskAUC:Absorbance") && channel.contains("S") )
10613  channel = channel.replace("S","A");
10614  qDebug() << "[isSet_to_analyse()] channel2 -- " << channel;
10615 
10616  QMap<QString, bool>::iterator jj;
10617  for ( jj = channels_to_analyse.begin(); jj != channels_to_analyse.end(); ++jj )
10618  {
10619  if ( jj.key().contains( channel ) && jj.key().contains( opsys ) )
10620  {
10621  if ( jj.value() )
10622  {
10623  qDebug() << "Triple " << triple_name << " of channel (" << jj.key() << " will be analysed.";
10624  have_run = true;
10625  break;
10626  }
10627  }
10628  }
10629 
10630  return have_run;
10631 }

10853 int US_Edit::create_autoflowAnalysis_record( US_DB2* db, QString& tripleName, QString& status_json )
10854 {

10856

10868  // return autoflowAnalysisID;
10869  // }

10894  << QString::number( autoflowID_passed );

10897  qDebug() << "Query: " << qry;
10898

10918 // Save edits for a triple
10919 void US_Edit::write_triple_auto( int trx )
10920 {
10921  triple_index = trx;
10922 
10923  index_data_auto( trx );
10924 
10925  edata = outData[ data_index ];
10926  data = *edata;
10927 
10928  QString editGUID;
10929  QString editID;
10930  QString rawGUID;
10931  QString triple;
10932  QString ss;
10933  is_spike_auto = false;
10934 
10935  int odax = trx;
10936  int idax = odax;
10937 
10938  // Base parameters for triple:
10939  QString triple_name = cb_triple->itemText( trx );
10940 
10941  le_status->setText( tr( "Saving edit profile for channel %1" ).arg( triple_name ) );
10942  qApp->processEvents();
10943 
10944  scanExcl_begin_ind = editProfile_scans_excl[ triple_name ][0].toInt();
10945  scanExcl_end_ind = editProfile_scans_excl[ triple_name ][1].toInt();
10946 
10947  meniscus = editProfile[ triple_name ][0].toDouble();
10948  range_left = editProfile[ triple_name ][1].toDouble();
10949  range_right = editProfile[ triple_name ][2].toDouble();
10950  plateau = editProfile[ triple_name ][3].toDouble();
10951  baseline = editProfile[ triple_name ][4].toDouble();
10952 
10953 
10954  //also, for ABDE, deal with includes / excludes : includes = ...
10955  if ( autoflow_expType == "ABDE" )
10956  {
10957  includes = editProfile_includes[ triple_name ];
10958 
10959  QString wvl_c;
10960  if ( isMwl )
10961  {
10962  int wvx = cb_lplot ->currentIndex();
10963  wvl_c = expc_wvlns[ wvx ];
10964  }
10965  else
10966  wvl_c = triple_name.split("/")[2].trimmed();
10967 
10968  bl_corr_slope = editProfile_blc[ triple_name ][ wvl_c ][0].toDouble();
10969  bl_corr_yintercept = editProfile_blc[ triple_name ][ wvl_c ][1].toDouble();
10970  }
10971 
10972  if ( dataType == "IP" )
10973  {
10974  airGap_left = editProfile[ triple_name ][7].toDouble();
10975  airGap_right = editProfile[ triple_name ][8].toDouble();
10976  }
10977

11618  tr( "Cannot find any edit records in the database.\n" ) );
11619 
11620  return;
11621  }
11622 
11623  int index;
11624  US_GetEdit dialog( index, filenames );
11625  if ( dialog.exec() == QDialog::Rejected ) return;
11626 
11627  if ( index < 0 )
11628  return;
11629 
11630  filename = filenames[ index ];
11631  int dataID = editDataIDs[ index ].toInt();
11632 
11633  editLabel = filename.section( ".", -6, -6 );
11634  filename = workingDir + filename;
11635  db.readBlobFromDB( filename, "download_editData", dataID );
11636 
11637  cefnames << filename; // save the first file name
11638 
11639  // Loop to get files with same Edit Label from other triples
11640  for ( int ii = 1; ii < outData.size(); ii++ )
11641  {
11642  data = *outData[ ii ];
11643  q.clear();
11644  q << "get_rawDataID_from_GUID"
11645  << US_Util::uuid_unparse( (uchar*)data.rawGUID );
11646  db.query( q );
11647  db.next();
11648  rawDataID = db.value( 0 ).toString();
11649 
11650  q.clear();
11651  q << "get_editedDataIDs" << rawDataID;
11652  db.query( q );
11653  filename.clear();
11654  bool found = false;
11655 
11656  while ( db.next() )
11657  {
11658  dataID = db.value( 0 ).toString().toInt();
11659  filename = db.value( 2 ).toString();
11660  QString elb = filename.section( ".", -6, -6 );
11661 
11662  if ( elb == editLabel )
11663  {
11664  found = true;
11665  filename = workingDir + filename;
11666  db.readBlobFromDB( filename, "download_editData", dataID );
11667  cefnames << filename;
11668  break;
11669  }
11670  }
11671 
11672  if ( ! found )
11673  cefnames << "";
11674  }
11675  }
11676 
11677  else
11678  { // Get prior equilibrium edits from Local Disk
11679  QString filter = files[ cb_triple->currentIndex() ];
11680  index1 = filter.indexOf( '.' ) + 1;
11681 
11682  filter.insert( index1, "*." );
11683  filter.replace( QRegExp( "auc$" ), "xml" );
11684 
11685  // Ask for edit file
11686  filename = QFileDialog::getOpenFileName( this,
11687  tr( "Select a saved edit file" ),
11688  workingDir, filter );
11689 
11690  if ( filename.isEmpty() ) return;
11691 
11692  filename = filename.replace( "\\", "/" );
11693  editLabel = filename.section( "/", -1, -1 ).section( ".", -6, -6 );
11694  QString runID = filename.section( "/", -1, -1 ).section( ".", 0, -7 );
11695 
11696  for ( int ii = 0; ii < files.size(); ii++ )
11697  {
11698  filename = files[ ii ];
11699  filename = runID + "." + editLabel + "."
11700  + filename.section( ".", -5, -2 ) + ".xml";
11701  filename = workingDir + filename;
11702 
11703  if ( QFile( filename ).exists() )
11704  cefnames << filename;
11705 
11706  else
11707  cefnames << "";
11708  }
11709  }
11710 
11711  for ( int ii = 0; ii < cefnames.size(); ii++ )
11712  { // Read and apply edits from edit files
11713  data = *outData[ ii ];
11714  filename = cefnames[ ii ];
11715 
11716  // Read the edits
11717  US_DataIO::EditValues parameters;
11718 
11719  int result = US_DataIO::readEdits( filename, parameters );
11720 
11721  if ( result != US_DataIO::OK )
11722  {
11723  QMessageBox::warning( this,
11724  tr( "XML Error" ),
11725  tr( "An error occurred when reading edit file\n\n" )
11726  + US_DataIO::errorString( result ) );
11727  continue;
11728  }
11729 
11730  QString uuid = US_Util::uuid_unparse( (unsigned char*)data.rawGUID );
11731 
11732  if ( parameters.dataGUID != uuid )
11733  {
11734  QMessageBox::warning( this,
11735  tr( "Data Error" ),
11736  tr( "The edit file was not created using the current data" ) );
11737  continue;
11738  }
11739 
11740  // Apply the edits
11741  QString wkstr;
11742 
11743  meniscus = parameters.meniscus;
11744  range_left = parameters.rangeLeft;
11745  range_right = parameters.rangeRight;
11746  plateau = parameters.plateau;
11747  baseline = parameters.baseline;
11748 
11749  if ( parameters.speedData.size() > 0 )
11750  {
11751  meniscus = parameters.speedData[ 0 ].meniscus;
11752  range_left = parameters.speedData[ 0 ].dataLeft;
11753  range_right = parameters.speedData[ 0 ].dataRight;
11754  baseline = range_left;
11755  plateau = range_right;
11756 
11757  int jsd = sd_offs[ ii ];
11758 
11759  for ( int jj = 0; jj < sd_knts[ ii ]; jj++ )
11760  sData[ jsd++ ] = parameters.speedData[ jj ];
11761  }
11762 
11763  le_meniscus->setText( wkstr.sprintf( "%.3f", meniscus ) );
11764  pb_meniscus->setIcon( check );
11765  pb_meniscus->setEnabled( true );
11766 
11767  airGap_left = parameters.airGapLeft;
11768  airGap_right = parameters.airGapRight;
11769 
11770  if ( dataType == "IP" )
11771  {
11772  US_DataIO::adjust_interference( data, parameters );
11773  US_DataIO::calc_integral ( data, parameters );
11774  le_airGap->setText( wkstr.sprintf( "%.3f - %.3f",
11775  airGap_left, airGap_right ) );
11776  pb_airGap->setIcon( check );
11777  pb_airGap->setEnabled( true );
11778  }
11779 
11780  le_dataRange->setText( wkstr.sprintf( "%.3f - %.3f",
11781  range_left, range_right ) );
11782  le_dataStart->setText( QString::number( range_left, 'f', 8 ) );
11783  le_dataEnd ->setText( QString::number( range_right, 'f', 8 ) );
11784  pb_dataEnd ->setIcon( check );
11785  pb_dataEnd ->setEnabled( true );
11786  plateau = range_right - _PLATEAU_OFFSET_;
11787  le_plateau ->setText( QString::number( plateau, 'f', 8 ) );
11788 
11789  // Invert
11790  invert = parameters.invert;
11791 
11792  if ( invert == -1.0 ) pb_invert->setIcon( check );
11793  else pb_invert->setIcon( QIcon() );
11794 
11795  // Excluded scans
11796  init_includes();
11797  reset_excludes(); // Zero exclude combo boxes
11798  qSort( parameters.excludes );
11799 
11800  for ( int i = parameters.excludes.size(); i > 0; i-- )
11801  includes.removeAt( parameters.excludes[ i - 1 ] );
11802 
11803  // Edited points
11804  changed_points.clear();
11805 
11806  for ( int i = 0; i < parameters.editedPoints.size(); i++ )
11807  {
11808  int scan = parameters.editedPoints[ i ].scan;
11809  int index1 = (int)parameters.editedPoints[ i ].radius;
11810  double value = parameters.editedPoints[ i ].value;
11811 
11812  Edits e;
11813  e.scan = scan;
11814  e.changes << QPointF( index1, value );
11815 
11816  changed_points << e;
11817 
11818  data.scanData[ scan ].rvalues[ index1 ] = value;
11819  }
11820 
11821  // Spikes
11822  spikes = parameters.removeSpikes;
11823 
11824  pb_spikes->setIcon( QIcon() );
11825  pb_spikes->setEnabled( true );
11826  if ( spikes ) remove_spikes();
11827 
11828  // Noise
11829  noise_order = parameters.noiseOrder;
11830  if ( noise_order > 0 )
11831  {
11832  US_RiNoise::calc_residuals( data, includes, range_left, range_right,
11833  noise_order, residuals );
11834 
11835  subtract_residuals();
11836  }
11837  else
11838  {
11839  pb_noise ->setIcon( QIcon() );
11840  pb_residuals->setIcon( QIcon() );
11841  pb_residuals->setEnabled( false );
11842  }
11843 
11844  // Floating data
11845  floatingData = parameters.floatingData;
11846 
11847  if ( floatingData )
11848  pb_float->setIcon( check );
11849 
11850  else
11851  pb_float->setIcon( QIcon() );
11852  }
11853 
11854  step = FINISHED;
11855  set_pbColors( NULL );
11856 
11857  pb_report ->setEnabled( true );
11858  pb_undo ->setEnabled( true );
11859  pb_write ->setEnabled( true );
11860  ck_writemwl->setEnabled( isMwl );
11861 
11862  cndxt = ( cndxt < 0 ) ? 0 : cndxt;
11863  cndxs = ( cndxs < 0 ) ? 0 : cndxs;
11864  cb_triple->setCurrentIndex( cndxt );
11865  cb_rpms ->setCurrentIndex( cndxs );
11866 
11867  //changes_made= false;
11868  //plot_range();
11869 
11870  pb_reviewep->setEnabled( true );
11871  pb_nexteqtr->setEnabled( true );
11872 
11873  all_edits = all_edits_done();
11874  pb_report ->setEnabled( all_edits );
11875  pb_write ->setEnabled( all_edits );
11876  ck_writemwl->setEnabled( all_edits && isMwl );
11877  changes_made = all_edits;
11878 
11879  review_edits();
11880 }

12003 // Evaluate whether all edits are complete
12004 bool US_Edit::all_edits_done( void )
12005 {
12006  bool all_ed_done = false;
12007 
12008  if ( expIsEquil )
12009  {
12010  total_edits = 0;
12011  total_speeds = 0;
12012 
12013  for ( int jd = 0; jd < outData.size(); jd++ )
12014  { // Examine each data set to evaluate whether edits complete
12015  int jsd = sd_offs[ jd ];
12016  int ksd = jsd + sd_knts[ jd ];
12017  QList< double > drpms;
12018  US_DataIO::RawData* rawdat = outData[ jd ];
12019 
12020  // Count edits done on this data set
12021  for ( int js = jsd; js < ksd; js++ )
12022  {
12023  if ( sData[ js ].meniscus > 0.0 )
12024  total_edits++;
12025  }
12026 
12027  // Count speeds present in this data set
12028  for ( int js = 0; js < rawdat->scanData.size(); js++ )
12029  {
12030  double drpm = rawdat->scanData[ js ].rpm;
12031 
12032  if ( ! drpms.contains( drpm ) )
12033  drpms << drpm;
12034  }
12035 
12036  total_speeds += drpms.size();
12037  }
12038 
12039  // Set flag: are all edits complete?
12040  all_ed_done = ( total_edits == total_speeds );
12041  }
12042 
12043  else
12044  {
12045  all_ed_done = ( range_left != 0 &&
12046  range_right != 0 &&
12047  plateau != 0 &&
12048  baseline != 0 );
12049  }
12050 
12051 DbgLv(1) << "all_ed_done" << all_ed_done;
12052  return all_ed_done;
12053 }

12216 // Lambda Start has changed
12217 void US_Edit::lambda_start_value( int value )
12218 {
12219  int new_slambda = cb_lstart->itemText( value ).toInt();
12220  if ( new_slambda == slambda ) // check if new start is same as current start -> skip every update
12221  {
12222  return;
12223  }
12224  else if ( new_slambda > elambda ) // check if new start is greater than end
12225  {
12226  // if so, set start to end
12227  slambda = elambda;
12228  elambda = new_slambda;
12229  cb_lstart->setCurrentIndex( cb_lstart->findText( QString::number( slambda ) ) );
12230  cb_lend ->setCurrentIndex( cb_lend ->findText( QString::number( elambda ) ) );
12231  }
12232  else
12233  {
12234  slambda = cb_lstart->itemText( value ).toInt();
12235  }
12236  DbgLv(1) << "lambda_start_value value" << value << slambda;
12237 
12238  reset_plot_lambdas();
12239 }
12240 
12241 // Lambda End has changed
12242 void US_Edit::lambda_end_value( int value )
12243 {
12244  int new_elambda = cb_lend->itemText( value ).toInt();
12245  if ( new_elambda == elambda ) // check if new end is same as current end -> skip every update
12246  {
12247  return;
12248  }
12249  else if ( new_elambda < slambda ) // check if new end is less than start
12250  {
12251  // if so, set end to start
12252  elambda = slambda;
12253  slambda = new_elambda;
12254  cb_lstart->setCurrentIndex( cb_lstart->findText( QString::number( slambda ) ) );
12255  cb_lend ->setCurrentIndex( cb_lend ->findText( QString::number( elambda ) ) );
12256  }
12257  else
12258  {
12259  elambda = cb_lend ->itemText( value ).toInt();
12260  }

12263  reset_plot_lambdas();
