12266 // Adjust the plot wavelengths list, after a lambda range change
12267 void US_Edit::reset_plot_lambdas()
12268 {
12269  dlambda = (int)ct_ldelta->value();
12270  slambda = cb_lstart->currentText().toInt();
12271  elambda = cb_lend ->currentText().toInt();
12272  int plambd = cb_lplot ->currentText().toInt();
12273  int strtx = rawi_wvlns.indexOf( slambda );
12274  int endx = rawi_wvlns.indexOf( elambda ) + 1;
12275  int plotx = cb_lplot ->currentIndex();
12276 DbgLv(1) << "rpl: dl sl el px" << dlambda << slambda << elambda << plotx
12277  << "sx ex nr" << strtx << endx << rawc_wvlns.size();
12278 DbgLv(1) << "rpl: trx" << triple_index << cb_triple->currentIndex();
12279 DbgLv(1) << "rpl: rcw 0 1 m n" << rawc_wvlns[0] << rawc_wvlns[1]
12280  << rawc_wvlns[nwaveln-2] << rawc_wvlns[nwaveln-1];
12281  expc_wvlns.clear();
12282  expi_wvlns.clear();
12283 
12284  for ( int ii = strtx; ii < endx; ii += dlambda )
12285  { // Accumulate new list of export lambdas by looking at all raw lambas
12286  QString clam = rawc_wvlns[ ii ];
12287  int rlam = clam.toInt(); // Current raw input lambda
12288  expc_wvlns << clam;
12289  expi_wvlns << rlam;
12290  }
12291 
12292  nwavelo = expi_wvlns.size();
12293  plotx = qMax( 0, expi_wvlns.indexOf( plambd ) );
12294  plotx = ( plotx < nwavelo ) ? plotx : ( nwavelo / 2 );
12295 DbgLv(1) << "rpl: nwavelo plotx" << nwavelo << plotx;
12296 DbgLv(1) << "rpl: pl1 pln" << expi_wvlns[0] << expi_wvlns[nwavelo-1];
12297 
12298  if ( xaxis_radius )
12299  { // If x-axis is radius, reset wavelength-to-plot list
12300  cb_lplot->disconnect();
12301  cb_lplot->clear();
12302  cb_lplot->addItems( expc_wvlns );
12303  connect( cb_lplot, SIGNAL( currentIndexChanged( int ) ),
12304  this, SLOT ( lambda_plot_value ( int ) ) );
12305  cb_lplot->setCurrentIndex( plotx );
12306  }
12307 
12308  // Report export lambda range
12309  le_lxrng ->setText( tr( "%1 MWL exports: %2 %3 to %4," )
12310  .arg( nwavelo ).arg( chlamb ).arg( slambda ).arg( elambda )
12311  + ( lsel_range ? tr( " raw index increment %1." ).arg( dlambda )
12312  : tr( " from custom selections." ) ) );
12313 
12314  mwl_data.set_lambdas( expi_wvlns, triple_index );
12315  std::sort( expi_wvlns.begin(), expi_wvlns.end() );
12316 DbgLv(1) << "rpl: set_lambdas() complete. trx" << triple_index;
12317 
12318  reset_outData();
12319 DbgLv(1) << "rpl: reset_outData() complete";
12320 }

12413 // Plot Lambda/Radius value has changed
12414 void US_Edit::lambda_plot_value( int value )
12415 {
12416  if ( value < 0 ) return;
12417 
12418  double menissv = meniscus;
12419  plotndx = value;
12420 
12421  if ( ! xaxis_radius )
12422  { // If plotting radius records, go straight to plotting
12423  plot_mwl();
12424  return;
12425  }
12426 
12427  // If plotting wavelength records, check need to re-do/un-do edits
12428  QString swavl = cb_lplot ->itemText( plotndx );
12429  QString triple = cb_triple->currentText() + " / " + swavl;
12430  int idax = triples.indexOf( triple );
12431  plotrec = swavl.toInt();
12432 DbgLv(1) << "lambda_plot_value value" << value << plotrec;
12433  QString fname = ( menissv != 0.0 ) ? editFnames[ idax ] : "none";
12434 
12435  //ALEXEY:
12436  if ( us_edit_auto_mode )
12437  {
12438  plot_mwl();
12439  if ( autoflow_expType == "ABDE")
12440  {
12441  //This must be before plotting: set current baseline parms
12442  set_current_bll_abde( cb_triple->currentText(), swavl );
12443  //then replot
12444  plot_range_and_blc( );
12445 
12446  }
12447  else
12448  plot_range();
12449  return;
12450  }
12452 
12453 
12454  if ( fname == "none" )
12455  { // New wavelength has no edit: turn off edits
12456  qDebug() << "Setting meniscus!!";
12457  set_meniscus();
12458  }
12459 
12460  else if ( fname != "same" )
12461  { // New wavelength has its own edit: apply it
12462 
12463  qDebug() << " Same: appluing edits --";
12464  US_DataIO::EditValues parameters;
12465 
12466  US_DataIO::readEdits( workingDir + fname, parameters );
12467 
12468  apply_edits( parameters );
12469  }
12470 
12471  else if ( step != MENISCUS )
12472  { // New wavelength has same edit as others in channel: make sure applied
12473 
12474  qDebug() << "FOR MWL: switching between wavelengths...";
12475  }
12476 
12477  plot_mwl();
12478 }

12832

12834  return;

12841  {

12844  if ( dbP == NULL || dbP->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )

12905 // Write edit to all wavelengths of the current cell/channel
12906 void US_Edit::write_mwl()
12907 {
12908  QString saved_info = le_info->text();
12909  QString str;
12910  if ( ! isMwl )
12911  {
12912  QMessageBox::warning( this,
12913  tr( "Invalid Selection" ),
12914  tr( "The \"Save to all Wavelengths\" button is only valid\n"
12915  "for MultiWavelength data. No Save will be performed." ) );
12916  return;
12917  }
12918 
12919  meniscus = le_meniscus->text().toDouble();
12920  baseline = data.xvalues[ data.xindex( range_left ) + 5 ];
12921 
12922  if ( expIsEquil )
12923  { // Equilibrium: set baseline,plateau as flag that those are "done"
12924  int jsd = sd_offs[ triple_index ];
12925  meniscus = sData[ jsd ].meniscus;
12926  range_left = sData[ jsd ].dataLeft;
12927  range_right = sData[ jsd ].dataRight;
12928  baseline = range_left;
12929  plateau = range_right;
12930  }
12931 
12932  // Check if complete
12933  if ( meniscus == 0.0 )
12934  str = tr( "meniscus" );
12935  else if ( dataType == "IP" && ( airGap_left == 0.0 || airGap_right == 9.0 ) )
12936  str = tr( "air gap" );
12937  else if ( range_left == 0.0 || range_right == 9.0 )
12938  str = tr( "data range" );
12939  else if ( plateau == 0.0 )
12940  str = tr( "plateau" );
12941  else if ( baseline == 0.0 )
12942  str = tr( "baseline" );
12943 
12944  if ( ! str.isEmpty() )
12945  {
12946  QMessageBox::information( this,
12947  tr( "Data missing" ),
12948  tr( "You must define the " ) + str +
12949  tr( " before writing the edit profile." ) );
12950  return;
12951  }
12952 
12953  QString sufx = "";
12954 
12955  // Ask for editLabel if not yet defined
12956  while ( editLabel.isEmpty() )
12957  {
12958  QString now = QDateTime::currentDateTime()
12959  .toUTC().toString( "yyMMddhhmm" );
12960 
12961  bool ok;
12962  QString msg = tr( "The base Edit Label for this edit session is <b>" )
12963  + now + "</b> .<br/>"
12964  + tr( "You may add an optional suffix to further distinquish<br/>"
12965  "the Edit Label. Use alphanumeric characters, underscores,<br/>"
12966  "or hyphens (no spaces). Enter 0 to 10 suffix characters." );
12967  sufx = QInputDialog::getText( this,
12968  tr( "Create a unique session Edit Label" ),
12969  msg,
12970  QLineEdit::Normal,
12971  sufx,
12972  &ok );
12973 
12974  if ( ! ok ) return;
12975 
12976  sufx.remove( QRegExp( "[^\\w\\d_-]" ) );
12977  editLabel = now + sufx;
12978 
12979  if ( editLabel.length() > 20 )
12980  {
12981  QMessageBox::critical( this,
12982  tr( "Text length error" ),
12983  tr( "You entered %1 characters for the Edit Label suffix.\n"
12984  "Re-enter, limiting length to 10 characters." )
12985  .arg( sufx.length() ) );
12986  editLabel.clear();
12987  sufx = sufx.left( 10 );
12988  }
12989  }
12990 
12991  QVector< int > oldi_wvlns;
12992  int kwavelo = mwl_data.lambdas( oldi_wvlns );
12993  std::sort(oldi_wvlns.begin(), oldi_wvlns.end());
12994  int nwavelo = expi_wvlns.count();
12995  int wvx;
12996  bool chg_lamb = ( kwavelo != nwavelo );
12997 
12998  if ( ! chg_lamb )
12999  { // If no change in number of wavelengths, check actual lists
13000  for ( wvx = 0; wvx < nwavelo; wvx++ )
13001  {
13002  if ( oldi_wvlns[ wvx ] != expi_wvlns[ wvx ] )
13003  { // There is a difference in the lists: mark as such
13004  chg_lamb = true;
13005  break;
13006  }
13007  }
13008  }
13009 
13010  if ( chg_lamb )
13011  { // If wavelengths have changed, save new list and rebuild some vectors
13012  mwl_data.set_lambdas( expi_wvlns ); // Save new lambdas for channel
13013  std::sort( expi_wvlns.begin(), expi_wvlns.end() );
13014  reset_outData();
13015  }
13016 
13017  QString celchn = celchns.at( triple_index );
13018  QString scell = celchn.section( "/", 0, 0 ).simplified();
13019  QString schan = celchn.section( "/", 1, 1 ).simplified();
13020  QString tripbase = scell + " / " + schan + " / ";
13021  int idax = triples.indexOf( tripbase + expc_wvlns[ 0 ] );
13022  int odax = index_data( 0 );
13023 DbgLv(1) << "EDT:WrMwl: dax celchn" << odax << celchn;
13024 
13025  QString filebase = files[ idax ].section( ".", 0, -6 )
13026  + "." + editLabel + "."
13027  + files[ idax ].section( ".", -5, -5 )
13028  + "." + scell + "." + schan + ".";
13029  QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor ) );
13030 
13031  // Loop to output a file/db-record for each wavelength of the cell/channel
13032 
13033 DbgLv(1) << "EDT:WrMwl: files,wvlns.size" << files.size() << expc_wvlns.size();
13034  for ( wvx = 0; wvx < expc_wvlns.size(); wvx++ )
13035  {
13036  QString swavl = expc_wvlns[ wvx ];
13037  QString triple = tripbase + swavl;
13038  QString filename = filebase + swavl + ".xml";
13039  idax = triples.indexOf( triple );
13040  odax = index_data( wvx );
13041 DbgLv(1) << "EDT:WrMwl: wvx triple" << wvx << triple << "filename" << filename;
13042 
13043 DbgLv(1) << "EDT:WrMwl: idax,editGUIDs.size" << idax << editGUIDs.size();
13044  QString editGUID = editGUIDs[ idax ];
13045 
13046  if ( editGUID.isEmpty() )
13047  {
13048  editGUID = US_Util::new_guid();
13049  editGUIDs.replace( idax, editGUID );
13050  }
13051 DbgLv(1) << "EDT:WrMwl: editGUID" << editGUID;
13052 
13053 DbgLv(1) << "EDT:WrMwl: odax,outData.size" << odax << outData.size();
13054  QString rawGUID = US_Util::uuid_unparse(
13055  (unsigned char*)outData[ odax ]->rawGUID );
13056 DbgLv(1) << "EDT:WrMwl: rawGUID" << rawGUID;
13057 
13058  // Output the edit XML file
13059  le_info->setText( tr( "Writing " ) + filename + " ..." );
13060  qApp->processEvents();
13061  int wrstat = write_xml_file( filename, triple, editGUID, rawGUID );
13062 DbgLv(1) << "EDT:WrMwl: write_xml_file stat" << wrstat;
13063 
13064  if ( wrstat != 0 )
13065  return;
13066  else
13067  editFnames[ idax ] = filename;
13068 
13069  if ( disk_controls->db() )
13070  {
13071  if ( dbP == NULL )
13072  {
13073  US_Passwd pw;
13074  dbP = new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() );
13075  if ( dbP == NULL || dbP->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
13076  {
13077  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Connection Problem" ),
13078  tr( "Could not connect to database \n" ) + dbP->lastError() );
13079  return;
13080  }
13081  }
13082 
13083  QString editID = editIDs[ idax ];
13084 
13085  // Output the edit database record
13086  wrstat = write_edit_db( dbP, filename, editGUID, editID, rawGUID );
13087 DbgLv(1) << "EDT:WrMwl: dax fname" << idax << filename << "wrstat" << wrstat;
13088 
13089  if ( wrstat != 0 )
13090  return;
13091  } // END: DB output
13092  } // END: wavelength-in-cellchannel loop
13093 
13094  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
13095  changes_made = false;
13096  pb_report ->setEnabled( false );
13097  pb_write ->setEnabled( false );
13098  ck_writemwl ->setEnabled( false );

13104 // Write edit xml file
13105 int US_Edit::write_xml_file( QString& fname, QString& triple,
13106  QString& editGUID, QString& rawGUID )
13107 {
13108  QFile efo( workingDir + fname );
13109 
13110  if ( ! efo.open( QFile::WriteOnly | QFile::Text ) )
13111  {
13112  QMessageBox::information( this,
13113  tr( "File write error" ),
13114  tr( "Could not open the file\n" ) + workingDir + fname
13115  + tr( "\n for writing. Check your permissions." ) );
13116  return 1;
13117  }
13118 
13119 DbgLv(1) << "EDT:WrXml: IN: fname,triple,editGUID,rawGUID"
13120  << fname << triple << editGUID << rawGUID;
13121  QXmlStreamWriter xml( &efo );
13122 
13123  xml.setAutoFormatting( true );
13124  xml.writeStartDocument();
13125  xml.writeDTD ( "<!DOCTYPE UltraScanEdits>" );
13126  xml.writeStartElement( "experiment" );
13127  xml.writeAttribute ( "type", expType );
13128 
13129  // Write identification
13130  xml.writeStartElement( "identification" );
13131 
13132  xml.writeStartElement( "runid" );
13133  xml.writeAttribute ( "value", runID );
13134  xml.writeEndElement ();
13135 
13136  xml.writeStartElement( "editGUID" );
13137  xml.writeAttribute ( "value", editGUID );
13138  xml.writeEndElement ();
13139 
13140  xml.writeStartElement( "rawDataGUID" );
13141  xml.writeAttribute ( "value", rawGUID );
13142  xml.writeEndElement ();
13143 
13144  xml.writeEndElement (); // identification
13145 
13146  QStringList parts = triple.contains( " / " ) ?
13147  triple.split( " / " ) :
13148  triple.split( "." );
13149 DbgLv(1) << "EDT:WrXml: parts.size" << parts.size();
13150 
13151  QString cell = parts[ 0 ];
13152  QString channel = parts[ 1 ];
13153  QString waveln = parts[ 2 ];
13154 
13155 DbgLv(1) << "EDT:WrXml: waveln" << waveln;
13156 
13157  xml.writeStartElement( "run" );
13158  xml.writeAttribute ( "cell", cell );
13159  xml.writeAttribute ( "channel", channel );
13160  xml.writeAttribute ( "wavelength", waveln );
13161 
13162  // Write excluded scans
13163  if ( us_edit_auto_mode ) //<-- write excluded scans (beg|end) based on AProfile
13164  {
13165  xml.writeStartElement( "excludes" );
13166 
13167  //beginning of the scan set
13168  for ( int ii = 0; ii < scanExcl_begin_ind; ii++ )
13169  {
13170  xml.writeStartElement( "exclude" );
13171  xml.writeAttribute ( "scan", QString::number( ii ) );
13172  xml.writeEndElement ();
13173  }
13174 
13175  //end of the scan set
13176  for ( int ii = data.scanData.size() - scanExcl_end_ind; ii < data.scanData.size(); ii++ )
13177  {
13178  xml.writeStartElement( "exclude" );
13179  xml.writeAttribute ( "scan", QString::number( ii ) );
13180  xml.writeEndElement ();
13181  }
13182 
13183 
13184  //Also, for ABDE, exclude what was excluded manually for each triple
13185  for ( int ii = 0; ii < data.scanData.size(); ii++ )
13186  {
13187  if ( ! includes.contains( ii ) &&
13188  ii >= scanExcl_begin_ind &&
13189  ii < data.scanData.size() - scanExcl_end_ind )
13190  {
13191  xml.writeStartElement( "exclude" );
13192  xml.writeAttribute ( "scan", QString::number( ii ) );
13193  xml.writeEndElement ();
13194  }
13195  }
13196 
13197  xml.writeEndElement (); // excludes
13198  }
13199  else
13200  {
13201  if ( data.scanData.size() > includes.size() )
13202  {
13203  xml.writeStartElement( "excludes" );
13204 
13205  for ( int ii = 0; ii < data.scanData.size(); ii++ )
13206  {
13207  if ( ! includes.contains( ii ) )
13208  {
13209  xml.writeStartElement( "exclude" );
13210  xml.writeAttribute ( "scan", QString::number( ii ) );
13211  xml.writeEndElement ();
13212  }
13213  }
13214 
13215  xml.writeEndElement (); // excludes
13216  }
13217  }
13218 
13219  // Write edits
13220  if ( ! changed_points.isEmpty() )
13221  {
13222  xml.writeStartElement( "edited" );
13223 
13224  for ( int ii = 0; ii < changed_points.size(); ii++ )
13225  {
13226  Edits* e = &changed_points[ ii ];
13227 
13228  for ( int jj = 0; jj < e->changes.size(); jj++ )
13229  {
13230  xml.writeStartElement( "edit" );
13231  xml.writeAttribute ( "scan", QString::number( e->scan ) );
13232  xml.writeAttribute ( "radius",
13233  QString::number( e->changes[ jj ].x(), 'f', 8 ) );
13234  xml.writeAttribute ( "value",
13235  QString::number( e->changes[ jj ].y(), 'f', 8 ) );
13236  xml.writeEndElement ();
13237  }
13238  }
13239 
13240  xml.writeEndElement (); // edited
13241  }
13242 
13243  // Write meniscus, range, plateau, baseline, odlimit
13244  xml.writeStartElement( "parameters" );
13245 
13246  if ( ! expIsEquil )
13247  { // non-Equilibrium
13248  xml.writeStartElement( "meniscus" );
13249  xml.writeAttribute ( "radius",
13250  QString::number( meniscus, 'f', 8 ) );
13251  xml.writeEndElement ();
13252  xml.writeStartElement( "bottom" );
13253  xml.writeAttribute ( "radius",
13254  QString::number( bottom, 'f', 8 ) );
13255  xml.writeEndElement ();
13256 
13257  if ( dataType == "IP" )
13258  {
13259  xml.writeStartElement( "air_gap" );
13260  xml.writeAttribute ( "left",
13261  QString::number( airGap_left, 'f', 8 ) );
13262  xml.writeAttribute ( "right",
13263  QString::number( airGap_right, 'f', 8 ) );
13264  xml.writeAttribute ( "tolerance",
13265  QString::number( ct_gaps->value(), 'f', 8 ) );
13266  xml.writeEndElement ();
13267  }
13268 
13269  xml.writeStartElement( "data_range" );
13270  xml.writeAttribute ( "left",
13271  QString::number( range_left, 'f', 8 ) );
13272  xml.writeAttribute ( "right",
13273  QString::number( range_right, 'f', 8 ) );
13274  xml.writeEndElement ();
13275 
13276  xml.writeStartElement( "plateau" );
13277  xml.writeAttribute ( "radius",
13278  QString::number( plateau, 'f', 8 ) );
13279  xml.writeEndElement ();
13280 
13281  xml.writeStartElement( "baseline" );
13282  xml.writeAttribute ( "radius",
13283  QString::number( baseline, 'f', 8 ) );
13284  xml.writeEndElement ();
13285 
13286  xml.writeStartElement( "od_limit" );
13287  xml.writeAttribute ( "value",
13288  QString::number( odlimit, 'f', 8 ) );
13289  xml.writeEndElement ();
13290 
13291  //[ABDE] linear-baseline-correction
13292  if ( autoflow_expType == "ABDE" )
13293  {
13294  xml.writeStartElement( "linear_baseline_correction" );
13295  xml.writeAttribute ( "slope",
13296  QString::number( bl_corr_slope, 'f', 8 ) );
13297  xml.writeAttribute ( "y_intercept",
13298  QString::number( bl_corr_yintercept, 'f', 8 ) );
13299  xml.writeEndElement ();
13300  }
13301  }
13302 
13303  else
13304  { // Equilibrium
13305  if ( dataType == "IP" )
13306  {
13307  xml.writeStartElement( "air_gap" );
13308  xml.writeAttribute ( "left",
13309  QString::number( airGap_left, 'f', 8 ) );
13310  xml.writeAttribute ( "right",
13311  QString::number( airGap_right, 'f', 8 ) );
13312  xml.writeAttribute ( "tolerance",
13313  QString::number( ct_gaps->value(), 'f', 8 ) );
13314  xml.writeEndElement ();
13315  }
13316 
13317  int jsd = sd_offs[ triple_index ];
13318  int ksd = jsd + sd_knts[ triple_index ];
13319 
13320  for ( int ii = jsd; ii < ksd; ii++ )
13321  {
13322  double speed = sData[ ii ].speed;
13323  int sStart = sData[ ii ].first_scan;
13324  int sCount = sData[ ii ].scan_count;
13325  double meniscus = sData[ ii ].meniscus;
13326  double dataLeft = sData[ ii ].dataLeft;
13327  double dataRight = sData[ ii ].dataRight;
13328 
13329  xml.writeStartElement( "speed" );
13330  xml.writeAttribute ( "value", QString::number( speed ) );
13331  xml.writeAttribute ( "scanStart", QString::number( sStart ) );
13332  xml.writeAttribute ( "scanCount", QString::number( sCount ) );
13333 
13334  xml.writeStartElement( "meniscus" );
13335  xml.writeAttribute ( "radius", QString::number( meniscus, 'f', 8 ) );
13336  xml.writeEndElement (); // meniscus
13337 
13338  xml.writeStartElement( "data_range" );
13339  xml.writeAttribute ( "left", QString::number( dataLeft, 'f', 8 ) );
13340  xml.writeAttribute ( "right", QString::number( dataRight, 'f', 8 ) );
13341  xml.writeEndElement (); // data_range
13342 
13343  xml.writeEndElement (); // speed
13344  }
13345  }
13346 
13347  xml.writeEndElement (); // parameters
13348 
13349  if ( ! pb_residuals->icon().isNull() ||
13350  ! pb_spikes->icon().isNull() ||
13351  invert == -1.0 ||
13352  floatingData ||
13353  is_spike_auto )
13354  {
13355  xml.writeStartElement( "operations" );
13356 
13357  // Write RI Noise
13358  if ( ! pb_residuals->icon().isNull() )
13359  {
13360  xml.writeStartElement( "subtract_ri_noise" );
13361  xml.writeAttribute ( "order", QString::number( noise_order ) );
13362  xml.writeEndElement ();
13363  }
13364 
13365  // Write Remove Spikes
13366  if ( !us_edit_auto_mode )
13367  {
13368  if ( ! pb_spikes->icon().isNull() )
13369  {
13370  xml.writeStartElement( "remove_spikes" );
13371  xml.writeEndElement ();
13372  }
13373  }
13374  else
13375  {
13376  if ( is_spike_auto )
13377  //if ( is_spike_auto || dataType == "IP" ) //ALEXEY: for now, for interference data which are processed manually....
13378  {
13379  xml.writeStartElement( "remove_spikes" );
13380  xml.writeEndElement ();
13381  }
13382  }
13383 
13384  // Write Invert
13385  if ( invert == -1.0 )
13386  {
13387  xml.writeStartElement( "invert" );
13388  xml.writeEndElement ();
13389  }
13390 
13391  // Write indication of floating data
13392  if ( floatingData )
13393  {
13394  xml.writeStartElement( "floating_data" );
13395  xml.writeEndElement ();
13396  }
13397 
13398  xml.writeEndElement (); // operations
13399  }
13400 
13401  xml.writeEndElement (); // run
13402  xml.writeEndElement (); // experiment
13403  xml.writeEndDocument ();
13404 
13405  efo.close();
13406  return 0;
13407 }

13409 // Write edit database record
13410 int US_Edit::write_edit_db( US_DB2* dbP, QString& fname, QString& editGUID,
13411  QString& editID, QString& rawGUID )
13412 {
13413  int idEdit;
13414 
13415  if ( dbP == NULL )
13416  {
13417  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Connection Problem" ),
13418  tr( "Could not connect to database \n" ) + dbP->lastError() );
13419  return 1;
13420  }
13421 
13422  QStringList query( "get_rawDataID_from_GUID" );
13423  query << rawGUID;
13424  dbP->query( query );
13425 
13426  if ( dbP->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
13427  {
13428  QMessageBox::warning( this,
13429  tr( "AUC Data is not in DB" ),
13430  tr( "Cannot save edit data to the database.\n"
13431  "The associated AUC data is not present." ) );
13432  return 2;
13433  }
13434 
13435  dbP->next();
13436  QString rawDataID = dbP->value( 0 ).toString();
13437 
13438 
13439  // Save edit file to DB
13440  query.clear();
13441 
13442  if ( editID.isEmpty() )
13443  {
13444  query << "new_editedData" << rawDataID << editGUID << runID
13445  << fname << "";
13446 
13447  dbP->query( query );
13448 
13449  if ( dbP->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
13450  {
13451  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Database Problem" ),
13452  tr( "Could not insert metadata into the database\n" ) +
13453  dbP->lastError() );
13454 
13455  return 3;
13456  }
13457 
13458  idEdit = dbP->lastInsertID();
13459  editID = QString::number( idEdit );
13460  int dax = editGUIDs.indexOf( editGUID );
13461  editIDs.replace( dax, editID );
13462  }
13463 
13464  else
13465  {
13466  query << "update_editedData" << editID << rawDataID << editGUID
13467  << runID << fname << "";
13468  dbP->query( query );
13469 
13470  if ( dbP->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
13471  {
13472  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Database Problem" ),
13473  tr( "Could not update metadata in the database \n" ) +
13474  dbP->lastError() );
13475 
13476  return 4;
13477  }
13478 
13479  idEdit = editID.toInt();
13480  }
13481 
13482  dbP->writeBlobToDB( workingDir + fname, "upload_editData", idEdit );
13483 
13484  if ( dbP->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
13485  {
13486  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Database Problem" ),
13487  tr( "Could not insert edit xml data into database \n" ) +
13488  dbP->lastError() );
13489  return 5;
13490  }
13491 
13492  return 0;
13493 }

13495 // Return the index in the output data of the current or specified wavelength
13496 int US_Edit::index_data_auto( int trx, int wvx )
13497 {
13498  triple_index = trx; // Triple index
13499  int odatx = triple_index; // Default output data index
13500 
13501  QString triple_name = cb_triple->itemText( trx );
13502 
13503  qDebug() << "Index_data_auto: triple_name, isMwl -- " << triple_name << isMwl;
13504 
13505  //Debug
13506  for ( int g=0; g < expi_wvlns.size(); ++g )
13507  qDebug() << "MWL wavelengths for triple: " << triple_name << expi_wvlns[ g ];
13508 
13509  if ( isMwl )
13510  { // For MWL, compute data index from wavelength and triple indexes
13511  if ( wvx < 0 )
13512  { // For the default case, use the current wavelength index
13513  plotndx = cb_lplot->currentIndex();
13514  int iwavl = expi_wvlns[ plotndx ]; //ALEXEY: do we need to set data in the middle of the triple set ??
13515 
13516  //int iwavl = expi_wvlns[ 0 ]; // ALEXEY: OR beginning of the set? ??
13517  data_index = mwl_data.data_index( iwavl, triple_index );
13518  odatx = data_index;
13519 DbgLv(1) << "IxDa_AUTO: dx" << data_index << "plx wavl trx"
13520  << plotndx << iwavl << triple_index;
13521  }
13522 
13523  else
13524  { // Use a specified wavelength index (and do not set internal value)
13525  int iwavl = expi_wvlns[ wvx ];
13526  odatx = mwl_data.data_index( iwavl, triple_index );
13527  }
13528  }
13529 
13530  else // for non-MWL, set data index internal value to triple index
13531  data_index = triple_index;
13532 
13533  qDebug() << "Triple index in INDEX_DATA: trx, wvx, data_index: " << triple_index << ", " << wvx << ", " << data_index;
13534 
13535  return odatx;
13536 }

13538 // Return the index in the output data of the current or specified wavelength
13539 int US_Edit::index_data( int wvx )
13540 {
13541  triple_index = cb_triple->currentIndex(); // Triple index
13542  int odatx = triple_index; // Default output data index
13543 
13544  if ( isMwl )
13545  { // For MWL, compute data index from wavelength and triple indexes
13546  if ( wvx < 0 )
13547  { // For the default case, use the current wavelength index
13548  if ( ! xaxis_radius ) return 0;
13549 
13550  plotndx = cb_lplot->currentIndex();
13551  int iwavl = expi_wvlns[ plotndx ];
13552  data_index = mwl_data.data_index( iwavl, triple_index );
13553  odatx = data_index;
13554 DbgLv(1) << "IxDa: dx" << data_index << "plx wavl trx"
13555  << plotndx << iwavl << triple_index;
13556  }
13557 
13558  else
13559  { // Use a specified wavelength index (and do not set internal value)
13560  int iwavl = expi_wvlns[ wvx ];
13561  odatx = mwl_data.data_index( iwavl, triple_index );
13562  }
13563  }
13564 
13565  else // for non-MWL, set data index internal value to triple index
13566  data_index = triple_index;
13567 
13568  return odatx;

13571 // Get a list of filenames with Edit Label like a specified file name
13572 int US_Edit::like_edit_files( QString filename, QStringList& editfiles,
13573  US_DB2* dbP )
13574 {
13575  // Determine local-disk files with same edit label and cell/channel
13576  QString filebase = filename.section( ".", 0, -3 );
13577  QStringList filter( filebase + ".*.xml" );
13578  QStringList edfiles = QDir( workingDir ).entryList(
13579  filter, QDir::Files, QDir::Name );
13580  QStringList ldfiles;
13581 
13582  // Pare down the list to those with triples matching loaded files
13583  for ( int ii = 0; ii < edfiles.count(); ii++ )
13584  {
13585  QString fname = edfiles[ ii ];
13586  QString triple = fname.section( ".", -4, -2 ).replace( ".", " / " );
13587 
13588  if ( triples.contains( triple ) )
13589  ldfiles << fname;
13590  }
13591 
13592  int nledits = ldfiles.count();
13593 DbgLv(1) << "LiEdFi: nledits" << ldfiles.count() << filter;
13594 
13595  if ( dbP != NULL )
13596  { // Determine database like files and compare to local
13597  QString invID = QString::number( US_Settings::us_inv_ID() );
13598  QStringList dbfiles;
13599  QStringList dbEdIds;
13600  QStringList dbquery;
13601 
13602  // Get the filenames and edit IDs for like-named files in the DB
13603  dbquery.clear();
13604  dbquery << "all_editedDataIDs" << invID;
13605  dbP->query( dbquery );
13606 
13607  while ( dbP->next() )
13608  { // Accumulate filenames and editIDs from the database
13609  QString idData = dbP->value( 0 ).toString();
13610  QString efname = dbP->value( 2 ).toString()
13611  .section( "/", -1, -1 );
13612  QString triple = efname.section( ".", -4, -2 )
13613  .replace( ".", " / " );
13614 //DbgLv(1) << "LiEdFi: db0,2" << idData << efname << "fbase" << filebase;
13615 
13616  // If the file name has a like edit label, has the same cell/channel,
13617  // and has triple matching a loaded file, save it.
13618  if ( efname.startsWith( filebase ) && triples.contains( triple ) )
13619  {
13620  dbfiles << efname;
13621  dbEdIds << idData;
13622 DbgLv(1) << "LiEdFi: id fn dbfsiz" << idData << efname << dbfiles.count();
13623  }
13624  }
13625 
13626  int nlocals = ldfiles.count();
13627  nledits = dbfiles.count();
13628 DbgLv(1) << "LiEdFi: nlocals nledits" << nlocals << nledits;
13629 
13630  if ( nledits != nlocals )
13631  { // DB records are not matched locally, so download from DB
13632  if ( nlocals == 0 )
13633  QDir().mkpath( workingDir );
13634 
13635  dbfiles.sort();
13636 
13637  for ( int ii = 0; ii < dbfiles.count(); ii++ )
13638  { // Download each DB record to a local file
13639  QString fname = workingDir + dbfiles[ ii ];
13640  int dataID = dbEdIds[ ii ].toInt();
13641 
13642  dbP->readBlobFromDB( fname, "download_editData", dataID );
13643  }
13644 
13645  ldfiles = dbfiles;
13646  }
13647  }
13648 
13649  editfiles = ldfiles;
13650  nledits = editfiles.count();
13651 
13652  if ( nledits == 0 )
13653  { // No files (should not happen): return at least the specified file name
13654  editfiles << filename;
13655  nledits = 1;
13656  }
13657 
13658  else if ( nledits > 1 )
13659  { // If multiple files, sort them
13660  editfiles.sort();
13661  }
13662 DbgLv(1) << "LiEdFi: nle fn0" << nledits << editfiles[0];
13663 
13664  return nledits;
13665 }
13666 
13667 // Apply edits to the current triple data
13668 int US_Edit::apply_edits( US_DataIO::EditValues parameters )
13669 {
13670  int status = 0;
13671 
13672  // Apply the edits with specified parameters
13673  QString wkstr;
13674 
13675  meniscus = parameters.meniscus;
13676  range_left = parameters.rangeLeft;
13677  range_right = parameters.rangeRight;
13678  plateau = parameters.plateau;
13679  baseline = parameters.baseline;
13680  odlimit = parameters.ODlimit;
13681 
13682  le_meniscus->setText( wkstr.sprintf( "%.3f", meniscus ) );
13683  pb_meniscus->setIcon( check );
13684  pb_meniscus->setEnabled( true );
13685 
13686  airGap_left = parameters.airGapLeft;
13687  airGap_right = parameters.airGapRight;
13688 
13689  if ( dataType == "IP" )
13690  {
13691  US_DataIO::adjust_interference( data, parameters );
13692  US_DataIO::calc_integral ( data, parameters );
13693  le_airGap->setText( wkstr.sprintf( "%.3f - %.3f",
13694  airGap_left, airGap_right ) );
13695  pb_airGap->setIcon( check );
13696  pb_airGap->setEnabled( true );
13697  }
13698 
13699  le_dataStart->setText( QString::number( range_left, 'f', 8 ) );
13700  le_dataEnd ->setText( QString::number( range_right, 'f', 8 ) );
13701  pb_dataEnd ->setIcon( check );
13702  pb_dataEnd ->setEnabled( true );
13703 
13704  plateau = range_right - _PLATEAU_OFFSET_;
13705  le_plateau ->setText( QString::number( plateau, 'f', 8 ) );
13706 
13707  US_DataIO::Scan scan = data.scanData.last();
13708  int pt = data.xindex( baseline );
13709  double sum = 0.0;
13710 
13711  // Average the value for +/- 5 points
13712  for ( int jj = pt - 5; jj <= pt + 5; jj++ )
13713  sum += scan.rvalues[ jj ];
13714 double bl=sum/11.0;
13715 DbgLv(1) << "BL: DD : baseline bl" << baseline << bl;
13716 
13717  le_baseline->setText( wkstr.sprintf( "%.3f (%.3e)", baseline, sum / 11.0 ) );
13718 
13719  // Invert
13720  invert = parameters.invert;
13721 
13722  if ( invert == -1.0 ) pb_invert->setIcon( check );
13723  else pb_invert->setIcon( QIcon() );
13724 
13725  // Excluded scans
13726  init_includes();
13727  reset_excludes(); // Zero exclude combo boxes
13728  qSort( parameters.excludes );
13729 
13730  for ( int ii = parameters.excludes.size(); ii > 0; ii-- )
13731  includes.removeAt( parameters.excludes[ ii - 1 ] );
13732 
13733  // Edited points
13734  changed_points.clear();
13735 
13736  for ( int ii = 0; ii < parameters.editedPoints.size(); ii++ )
13737  {
13738  int scan = parameters.editedPoints[ ii ].scan;
13739  int index1 = (int)parameters.editedPoints[ ii ].radius;
13740  double value = parameters.editedPoints[ ii ].value;
13741 
13742  Edits e;
13743  e.scan = scan;
13744  e.changes << QPointF( index1, value );
13745 
13746  changed_points << e;
13747 
13748  data.scanData[ scan ].rvalues[ index1 ] = value;
13749  }
13750 
13751  // Spikes
13752  spikes = parameters.removeSpikes;
13753 
13754  pb_spikes->setIcon( QIcon() );
13755  pb_spikes->setEnabled( true );
13756  if ( spikes ) remove_spikes();
13757 
13758  // Noise
13759  noise_order = parameters.noiseOrder;
13760  if ( noise_order > 0 )
13761  {
13762  US_RiNoise::calc_residuals( data, includes, range_left, range_right,
13763  noise_order, residuals );
13764 
13765  subtract_residuals();
13766  }
13767  else
13768  {
13769  pb_noise ->setIcon( QIcon() );
13770  pb_residuals->setIcon( QIcon() );
13771  pb_residuals->setEnabled( false );
13772  }
13773 
13774  // Floating data
13775  floatingData = parameters.floatingData;
13776  if ( floatingData )
13777  pb_float->setIcon( check );
13778  else
13779  pb_float->setIcon( QIcon() );
13780 
13781  ct_odlim->disconnect();
13782  ct_odlim->setValue( odlimit );
13783  connect( ct_odlim, SIGNAL( valueChanged ( double ) ),
13784  this, SLOT ( od_radius_limit ( double ) ) );
13785 
13786  set_pbColors( NULL );
13787  step = FINISHED;
13788 
13789  return status;
13790 }

13792 // Reset the output data pointer vector after change in wavelengths
13793 void US_Edit::reset_outData()
13794 {
13795  if ( ! isMwl ) return;
13796 
13797  outData.clear();
13798  QVector< int > ex_wvlns;
13799  int ccoff = 0;
13800 DbgLv(1) << "rsoD: aDa size" << allData.size() << "ncelchn" << ncelchn;
13801 
13802  for ( int ccx = 0; ccx < ncelchn; ccx++ )
13803  {
13804  lambdas_by_cell( ccx );
13805 
13806  int kwvln = mwl_data.lambdas( ex_wvlns, ccx );
13807  std::sort(ex_wvlns.begin(), ex_wvlns.end());
13808 DbgLv(1) << "rsoD: ccx kwv" << ccx << kwvln << ex_wvlns.size()
13809  << "nwv ccoff" << nwaveln << ccoff;
13810 
13811  for ( int wvo = 0; wvo < kwvln; wvo++ )
13812  {
13813  int iwavl = ex_wvlns[ wvo ];
13814  int idatx = ccoff + rawi_wvlns.indexOf( iwavl );
13815 //DbgLv(1) << "rsoD: wvo" << wvo << "wavl datx" << iwavl << idatx;
13816  outData << &allData[ idatx ];
13817  }
13818 
13819  ccoff += nwaveln;
13820 //DbgLv(1) << "rsoD: ccx ccoff" << ccx << ccoff;
13821  }
13822 DbgLv(1) << "rsoD: final ccoff" << ccoff << "aDa size" << allData.size()
13823  << "oDa size" << outData.size();
13824 }

13827 int US_Edit::lambdas_by_cell( int trx )

13830  nwaveln = rawi_wvlns.count();
13831 
13832  if ( lrng_bycell )
13833  {
13834  rawi_wvlns = wavelns_i[ ccx ];
13835  // sort rawi_wvlns

13837  nwaveln = rawi_wvlns.count();
13838  rawc_wvlns.clear();
13839 
13840  for ( int wvx = 0; wvx < nwaveln; wvx++ )
13841  {
13842  rawc_wvlns << QString::number( rawi_wvlns[ wvx ] );
13843  }
13844  }
13845 
13846  return nwaveln;
13847 }

13950  idEdit, tripdesc );

14042 // Compose HTML header string
14043 QString US_Edit::html_header( const QString title, const QString head1 )
14044 {
14045  int trx = index_data();
14046  QString triple = triples.at( trx );
14047  QStringList parts = triple.split( " / " );
14048  QString cell = parts[ 0 ];
14049  QString channel = parts[ 1 ];
14050  QString wvlen = parts[ 2 ];
14051  QString editID = editIDs[ trx ];
14052  QString editLbl = editLabel.isEmpty() ?
14053  editFnames[ trx ].section( ".", -6, -6 ) :
14054  editLabel;
14055 
14056  QString ss = QString( "<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n" );
14057  ss += "<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN\"\n";
14058  ss += " \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD"
14059  "/xhtml1-strict.dtd\">\n";
14060  ss += "<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\""
14061  " xml:lang=\"en\" lang=\"en\">\n";
14062  ss += " <head>\n";
14063  ss += " <title> " + title + " </title>\n";
14064  ss += " <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content="
14065  "\"text/html; charset=iso-8859-1\"/>\n";

14121 
14122 QString US_Edit::run_details( void )
14123 {
14124  US_DataIO::RawData* dd = outData[ index_data() ];
14125 
14126  int scsize = dd->scanData.size();
14127  // Temperature and raw speed data
14128  double sumte = 0.0;
14129  double sumrs = 0.0;
14130  double maxTemp = -1.0e99;
14131  double minTemp = 1.0e99;
14132 
14133  for ( int ii = 0; ii < scsize; ii++ )
14134  {
14135  double tt = dd->scanData[ ii ].temperature;
14136  sumte += tt;
14137  maxTemp = qMax( maxTemp, tt );
14138  minTemp = qMin( minTemp, tt );
14139  sumrs += dd->scanData[ ii ].rpm;
14140  }
14141 
14142  QString avgrspd = QString::number( sumrs / scsize, 'f', 1 );
14143  QString avgtemp = QString::number( sumte / scsize, 'f', 1 );
14144  QString ss = "\n" + indent( 4 )
14145  + tr( "<h3>Detailed Run Information:</h3>\n" )
14146  + indent( 4 ) + "<table>\n"
14147  + table_row( tr( "Cell Description:" ), dd->description )
14148  + table_row( tr( "Data Directory:" ), workingDir )
14149  + table_row( tr( "Average Rotor Speed:" ), avgrspd + " rpm" )
14150  + table_row( tr( "Average Temperature:" ), avgtemp + " " + MLDEGC );
14151 
14152  if ( maxTemp - minTemp <= US_Settings::tempTolerance() )
14153  ss += table_row( tr( "Temperature Variation:" ),
14154  tr( "Within tolerance" ) );
14155  else
14156  ss += table_row( tr( "Temperature Variation:" ),
14157  tr( "(!) OUTSIDE TOLERANCE (!)" ) );
14158 
14159  // Time data
14160  double time_correction = US_Math2::time_correction( allData );
14161  int minutes = (int)time_correction / 60;
14162  int seconds = (int)time_correction % 60;
14163 
14164  QString mm = ( minutes == 1 ) ? tr( " minute " ) : tr( " minutes " );
14165  QString sec = ( seconds == 1 ) ? tr( " second" ) : tr( " seconds" );
14166 
14167  ss += table_row( tr( "Time Correction:" ),
14168  QString::number( minutes ) + mm +
14169  QString::number( seconds ) + sec );
14170 
14171  double duration = allData.last().scanData.last().seconds;
14172 
14173  int hours = (int) duration / 3600;
14174  minutes = (int) duration / 60 - hours * 60;
14175  seconds = (int) duration % 60;
14176  QString ddType = QString( dd->type ).left( 2 );
14177  QString dataType = tr( "Absorbance:" );
14178  if ( ddType == "RI" ) dataType = tr( "Intensity:" );
14179  if ( ddType == "WI" ) dataType = tr( "Intensity:" );
14180  if ( ddType == "IP" ) dataType = tr( "Interference:" );
14181  if ( ddType == "FI" ) dataType = tr( "Fluorescence:" );
14182 
14183  QString hh;
14184  hh = ( hours == 1 ) ? tr( " hour " ) : tr( " hours " );
14185  mm = ( minutes == 1 ) ? tr( " minute " ) : tr( " minutes " );
14186  sec = ( seconds == 1 ) ? tr( " second" ) : tr( " seconds" );
14187 
14188  ss += table_row( tr( "Run Duration:" ),
14189  QString::number( hours ) + hh +
14190  QString::number( minutes ) + mm +
14191  QString::number( seconds ) + sec );
14192 
14193  // Wavelength, baseline, meniscus, range
14194  int iwvln = qRound( dd->scanData.last().wavelength );
14195  QString bln_od = QString( le_baseline->text() ).section( "(", 1, 1 )
14196  .section( ")", 0, 0 ) + " OD";
14197  QString left = le_dataStart->text();
14198  QString right = le_dataEnd ->text();
14199  QString plat = le_plateau->text();
14200 
14201  ss += table_row( tr( "Wavelength:" ),
14202  QString::number( iwvln ) + " nm" ) +
14203  table_row( tr( "Baseline " ) + dataType, bln_od );
14204  table_row( tr( "Meniscus Position:" ),
14205  le_meniscus->text() + " cm" );
14206 
14207 
14208  ss += table_row( tr( "Edited Data starts at:" ), left + " cm" ) +
14209  table_row( tr( "Edited Data stops at:" ), right + " cm " ) +
14210  table_row( tr( "Plateau Position:" ), plat + " cm" );
14211 
14212  ss += indent( 4 ) + "</table>\n";
14213 
14214  return ss;
14215 }

14330 QString US_Edit::scan_info( void )
14331 {
14332  US_DataIO::RawData* dd = outData[ index_data() ];
14333  double time_correction = US_Math2::time_correction( allData );
14334 
14335  QString ss = "\n" + indent( 4 ) + tr( "<h3>Scan Information:</h3>\n" )
14336  + indent( 4 ) + "<table>\n";
14337 
14338  ss += table_row( tr( "Scan" ), tr( "Corrected Time" ),
14339  tr( "Plateau Concentration" ),
14340  tr( "Seconds" ), tr( "Omega^2T" ), tr( "Raw Speed" ) );
14341 
14342  for ( int ii = 0; ii < dd->scanData.size(); ii++ )
14343  {
14344  QString s1;
14345  QString s2;
14346  QString s3;
14347  QString s4;
14348  QString s5;
14349  QString s6;
14350 
14351  double time = dd->scanData[ ii ].seconds;
14352  double omg2t = dd->scanData[ ii ].omega2t;
14353  double speed = dd->scanData[ ii ].rpm;
14354  int ctime = (int)( dd->scanData[ ii ].seconds - time_correction );
14355  int platx = US_DataIO::index( dd->xvalues, plateau );
14356  double od = dd->scanData[ ii ].rvalues[ platx ];
14357 
14358  s1 = s1.sprintf( "%4d", ii + 1 );
14359  s2 = s2.sprintf( "%4d min %2d sec", ctime / 60, ctime % 60 );
14360  s3 = s3.sprintf( "%.6f OD", od );
14361  s4 = s4.sprintf( "%5d", (int)time );
14362  s5 = s5.sprintf( "%.5e", omg2t );
14363  s6 = s6.sprintf( "%.1f", speed );
14364 
14365  ss += table_row( s1, s2, s3, s4, s5, s6 );
14366  }
14367 
14368  ss += indent( 4 ) + "</table>\n";
14369 
14370  return ss;
14371 }

14443 // Close edit after review of saved edits
14444 void US_Edit::pass_values( void )
14445 {
14446  //collect menicsus | airGap | baseline | range | etc data && pass to main edit stage
14447 
14448  QString triple_name = cb_triple->itemText( cb_triple->currentIndex() );
14449 
14450  QMap< QString, QStringList > editProfile_triple;
14451  QMap< QString, QList<int> > editProfile_triple_includes;
14452  QMap< QString, QStringList > editProfile_triple_blc;
14453 
14454  //make sure all principal params account for possible manual field edit:
14455  meniscus = le_meniscus->text().toDouble();
14456  range_right = le_dataEnd->text().toDouble();
14457 
14458  QStringList triple_params, triple_params_blc;
14459  triple_params << QString::number(meniscus)
14460  << QString::number(range_left)
14461  << QString::number(range_right)
14462  << QString::number(plateau)
14463  << QString::number(baseline)
14464  << QString::number(baseline_od)
14465  << QString("spike_false");
14466 
14467  //Linear-baseline-correction
14468  triple_params_blc << QString::number(bl_corr_slope)
14469  << QString::number(bl_corr_yintercept);
14470 
14471  if ( dataType == "IP" )
14472  {
14473  triple_params << QString::number(airGap_left)
14474  << QString::number(airGap_right);
14475  }
14476 
14477  editProfile_triple[ triple_name ] = triple_params;
14478  editProfile_triple_includes[ triple_name ] = includes;
14479  editProfile_triple_blc[ triple_name ] = triple_params_blc;
14480 
14481  qDebug() << "In PASSING values manually: triple_name, parms -- " << triple_name << editProfile_triple[ triple_name ];
14482  qDebug() << "In PASSING values manually: includes -- " << triple_name << editProfile_triple_includes[ triple_name ];
14483  qDebug() << "In PASSING values manually: linear-baseline-corr -- " << triple_name << editProfile_triple_blc[ triple_name ];
14484  qDebug() << "In PASSING values manually: us_edit_auto_mode BEFORE -- " << triple_name << us_edit_auto_mode;
14485 
14486  int status = QMessageBox::information( this,
14487  tr( "New Edit Parameters" ),
14488  tr( "This will overwrite current edit parameters. "
14489  "Do you want to proceed? " ),
14490  tr( "&OK" ), tr( "&Cancel" ),
14491  0, 0, 1 );
14492 
14493  if ( status != 0 ) return;
14494 
14495  emit pass_edit_params_includes( editProfile_triple_includes );
14496  emit pass_edit_params_blc( editProfile_triple_blc );
14497  emit pass_edit_params( editProfile_triple );
14498 
14499  close();
14500 }

14525 // Close edit after review of saved edits
14526 void US_Edit::close_edit( void )
14527 {
14528  int ntripls = allData.size();
14529  int nunedit = editFnames.count( QString( "none" ) );
14530 
14531  if ( nunedit > 0 )
14532  { // Some triples unedited: give option to cancel close
14533  QMessageBox mbox;
14534  QPushButton* pb_cancel;
14535  QPushButton* pb_doclose;
14536  QString msg = tr( "Edits have not been saved for<br/>"
14537  "%1 of %2 total triples.<br/></br/>"
14538  "Do you wish to<br/>"
14539  "&nbsp;&nbsp;"
14540  "return to edit more (<b>Cancel</b>) or<br/>"
14541  "&nbsp;&nbsp;"
14542  "close with current state (<b>Close</b>)<br/>?" )
14543  .arg( nunedit ).arg( ntripls );
14544  mbox.setIcon ( QMessageBox::Question );
14545  mbox.setTextFormat( Qt::RichText );
14546  mbox.setText ( msg );
14547  pb_cancel = mbox.addButton( tr( "Cancel" ),
14548  QMessageBox::RejectRole );
14549  pb_doclose = mbox.addButton( tr( "Close" ),
14550  QMessageBox::AcceptRole );
14551  mbox.setDefaultButton( pb_doclose );
14552  mbox.exec();
14553  if ( mbox.clickedButton() == pb_cancel )
14554  return;
14555  }
14556 
14557  close();
14558 }
